18¿é 38:1 Then the LORD answered Job out of the whirlwind and said,
18¿é 38:2 "Who is this that darkens counsel By words without knowledge?
18¿é 38:3 "Now gird up your loins like a man, And I will ask you, and you instruct Me!
18¿é 38:4 "Where were you when I laid the foundation of the earth? Tell [Me,] if you have understanding,
18¿é 38:5 Who set its measurements, since you know? Or who stretched the line on it?
18¿é 38:6 "On what were its bases sunk? Or who laid its cornerstone,
18¿é 38:7 When the morning stars sang together, And all the sons of God shouted for joy?
18¿é 38:8 "Or [who] enclosed the sea with doors, When, bursting forth, it went out from the womb;
18¿é 38:9 When I made a cloud its garment, And thick darkness its swaddling band,
18¿é 38:10 And I placed boundaries on it, And I set a bolt and doors,
18¿é 38:11 And I said, 'Thus far you shall come, but no farther; And here shall your proud waves stop'?
18¿é 38:12 "Have you ever in your life commanded the morning, [And] caused the dawn to know its place;
