18¿é 38:14 "It is changed like clay [under] the seal; And they stand forth like a garment.
18¿é 38:15 "And from the wicked their light is withheld, And the uplifted arm is broken.
18¿é 38:16 "Have you entered into the springs of the sea? Or have you walked in the recesses of the deep?
18¿é 38:17 "Have the gates of death been revealed to you? Or have you seen the gates of deep darkness?
18¿é 38:18 "Have you understood the expanse of the earth? Tell [Me,] if you know all this.
18¿é 38:19 "Where is the way to the dwelling of light? And darkness, where is its place,
18¿é 38:20 That you may take it to its territory, And that you may discern the paths to its home?
18¿é 38:21 "You know, for you were born then, And the number of your days is great!
18¿é 38:22 "Have you entered the storehouses of the snow, Or have you seen the storehouses of the hail,
18¿é 38:23 Which I have reserved for the time of distress, For the day of war and battle?
18¿é 38:24 "Where is the way that the light is divided, [Or] the east wind scattered on the earth?
18¿é 38:25 "Who has cleft a channel for the flood, Or a way for the thunderbolt;
18¿é 38:26 To bring rain on a land without people, [On] a desert without a man in it,
18¿é 38:27 To satisfy the waste and desolate land, And to make the seeds of grass to sprout?
18¿é 38:28 "Has the rain a father? Or who has begotten the drops of dew?
18¿é 38:29 "From whose womb has come the ice? And the frost of heaven, who has given it birth?
18¿é 38:30 "Water becomes hard like stone, And the surface of the deep is imprisoned.
18¿é 38:31 "Can you bind the chains of the Pleiades, Or loose the cords of Orion?
18¿é 38:32 "Can you lead forth a constellation in its season, And guide the Bear with her satellites?
18¿é 38:33 "Do you know the ordinances of the heavens, Or fix their rule over the earth?
18¿é 38:34 "Can you lift up your voice to the clouds, So that an abundance of water may cover you?
18¿é 38:35 "Can you send forth lightnings that they may go And say to you, 'Here we are'?
18¿é 38:36 "Who has put wisdom in the innermost being, Or has given understanding to the mind?
18¿é 38:37 "Who can count the clouds by wisdom, Or tip the water jars of the heavens,
18¿é 38:38 When the dust hardens into a mass, And the clods stick together?
18¿é 38:39 "Can you hunt the prey for the lion, Or satisfy the appetite of the young lions,
18¿é 38:40 When they crouch in [their] dens, [And] lie in wait in [their] lair?
18¿é 38:41 "Who prepares for the raven its nourishment, When its young cry to God, And wander about without food?
18¿é 39:1 "Do you know the time the mountain goats give birth? Do you observe the calving of the deer?
18¿é 39:2 "Can you count the months they fulfill, Or do you know the time they give birth?
18¿é 39:3 "They kneel down, they bring forth their young, They get rid of their labor pains.
18¿é 39:4 "Their offspring become strong, they grow up in the open field; They leave and do not return to them.
18¿é 39:5 "Who sent out the wild donkey free? And who loosed the bonds of the swift donkey,
18¿é 39:6 To whom I gave the wilderness for a home, And the salt land for his dwelling place?
18¿é 39:7 "He scorns the tumult of the city, The shoutings of the driver he does not hear.
18¿é 39:8 "He explores the mountains for his pasture, And he searches after every green thing.
18¿é 39:9 "Will the wild ox consent to serve you? Or will he spend the night at your manger?
