18¿é 39:15 And she forgets that a foot may crush them, Or that a wild beast may trample them.
18¿é 39:16 "She treats her young cruelly, as if [they] were not hers; Though her labor be in vain, [she] is unconcerned;
18¿é 39:17 Because God has made her forget wisdom, And has not given her a share of understanding.
18¿é 39:18 "When she lifts herself on high, She laughs at the horse and his rider.
