19½Ã 8:1 {For the choir director; on the Gittith. A Psalm of David.} O LORD, our Lord, How majestic is Thy name in all the earth, Who hast displayed Thy splendor above the heavens!
19½Ã 8:2 From the mouth of infants and nursing babes Thou hast established strength, Because of Thine adversaries, To make the enemy and the revengeful cease.
19½Ã 8:3 When I consider Thy heavens, the work of Thy fingers, The moon and the stars, which Thou hast ordained;
19½Ã 8:4 What is man, that Thou dost take thought of him? And the son of man, that Thou dost care for him?
