19½Ã 8:7 All sheep and oxen, And also the beasts of the field,
19½Ã 8:8 The birds of the heavens, and the fish of the sea, Whatever passes through the paths of the seas.
19½Ã 8:9 O LORD, our Lord, How majestic is Thy name in all the earth!
19½Ã 9:1 {For the choir director; on Muth-labben. A Psalm of David.} I will give thanks to the LORD with all my heart; I will tell of all Thy wonders.
19½Ã 9:2 I will be glad and exult in Thee; I will sing praise to Thy name, O Most High.
19½Ã 9:3 When my enemies turn back, They stumble and perish before Thee.
19½Ã 9:4 For Thou hast maintained my just cause; Thou dost sit on the throne judging righteously.
19½Ã 9:5 Thou hast rebuked the nations; Thou hast destroyed the wicked; Thou hast blotted out their name forever and ever.
19½Ã 9:6 The enemy has come to an end in perpetual ruins, And Thou hast uprooted the cities; The very memory of them has perished.
19½Ã 9:7 But the LORD abides forever; He has established His throne for judgment,
19½Ã 9:8 And He will judge the world in righteousness; He will execute judgment for the peoples with equity.
19½Ã 9:9 The LORD also will be a stronghold for the oppressed, A stronghold in times of trouble,
19½Ã 9:10 And those who know Thy name will put their trust in Thee; For Thou, O LORD, hast not forsaken those who seek Thee.
19½Ã 9:11 Sing praises to the LORD, who dwells in Zion; Declare among the peoples His deeds.
19½Ã 9:12 For He who requires blood remembers them; He does not forget the cry of the afflicted.
19½Ã 9:13 Be gracious to me, O LORD; Behold my affliction from those who hate me, Thou who dost lift me up from the gates of death;
