19½Ã 9:15 The nations have sunk down in the pit which they have made; In the net which they hid, their own foot has been caught.
19½Ã 9:16 The LORD has made Himself known; He has executed judgment. In the work of his own hands the wicked is snared. Higgaion Selah.
19½Ã 9:17 The wicked will return to Sheol, [Even] all the nations who forget God.
19½Ã 9:18 For the needy will not always be forgotten, Nor the hope of the afflicted perish forever.
19½Ã 9:19 Arise, O LORD, do not let man prevail; Let the nations be judged before Thee.
19½Ã 9:20 Put them in fear, O LORD; Let the nations know that they are but men. Selah.
19½Ã 10:1 Why dost Thou stand afar off, O LORD? Why dost Thou hide [Thyself] in times of trouble?
19½Ã 10:2 In pride the wicked hotly pursue the afflicted; Let them be caught in the plots which they have devised.
19½Ã 10:3 For the wicked boasts of his heart's desire, And the greedy man curses [and] spurns the LORD.
19½Ã 10:4 The wicked, in the haughtiness of his countenance, does not seek [Him.] All his thoughts are, "There is no God."
19½Ã 10:5 His ways prosper at all times; Thy judgments are on high, out of his sight; As for all his adversaries, he snorts at them.
19½Ã 10:6 He says to himself, "I shall not be moved; Throughout all generations I shall not be in adversity."
19½Ã 10:7 His mouth is full of curses and deceit and oppression; Under his tongue is mischief and wickedness.
19½Ã 10:8 He sits in the lurking places of the villages; In the hiding places he kills the innocent; His eyes stealthily watch for the unfortunate.
19½Ã 10:9 He lurks in a hiding place as a lion in his lair; He lurks to catch the afflicted; He catches the afflicted when he draws him into his net.
19½Ã 10:10 He crouches, he bows down, And the unfortunate fall by his mighty ones.
19½Ã 10:11 He says to himself, "God has forgotten; He has hidden His face; He will never see it."
