19½Ã 11:4 The LORD is in His holy temple; the Lord's throne is in heaven; His eyes behold, His eyelids test the sons of men.
19½Ã 11:5 The LORD tests the righteous and the wicked, And the one who loves violence His soul hates.
19½Ã 11:6 Upon the wicked He will rain snares; Fire and brimstone and burning wind will be the portion of their cup.
19½Ã 11:7 For the LORD is righteous; He loves righteousness; The upright will behold His face.
19½Ã 12:1 {For the choir director; upon an eight-stringed lyre. A Psalm of David.} Help, LORD, for the godly man ceases to be, For the faithful disappear from among the sons of men.
19½Ã 12:2 They speak falsehood to one another; With flattering lips and with a double heart they speak.
19½Ã 12:3 May the LORD cut off all flattering lips, The tongue that speaks great things;
19½Ã 12:4 Who have said, "With our tongue we will prevail; Our lips are our own; who is lord over us?"
