19½Ã 13:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} How long, O LORD? Wilt Thou forget me forever? How long wilt Thou hide Thy face from me?
19½Ã 13:2 How long shall I take counsel in my soul, [Having] sorrow in my heart all the day? How long will my enemy be exalted over me?
19½Ã 13:3 Consider [and] answer me, O LORD, my God; Enlighten my eyes, lest I sleep the [sleep of] death,
19½Ã 13:4 Lest my enemy say, "I have overcome him," [Lest] my adversaries rejoice when I am shaken.
19½Ã 13:5 But I have trusted in Thy lovingkindness; My heart shall rejoice in Thy salvation.
19½Ã 13:6 I will sing to the LORD, Because He has dealt bountifully with me.
19½Ã 14:1 {For the choir director. [A Psalm] of David.} The fool has said in his heart, "There is no God." They are corrupt, they have committed abominable deeds; There is no one who does good.
19½Ã 14:2 The LORD has looked down from heaven upon the sons of men, To see if there are any who understand, Who seek after God.
19½Ã 14:3 They have all turned aside; together they have become corrupt; There is no one who does good, not even one.
