19½Ã 14:5 There they are in great dread, For God is with the righteous generation.
19½Ã 14:6 You would put to shame the counsel of the afflicted, But the LORD is his refuge.
19½Ã 14:7 Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come out of Zion! When the LORD restores His captive people, Jacob will rejoice, Israel will be glad.
19½Ã 15:1 {A Psalm of David.} O LORD, who may abide in Thy tent? Who may dwell on Thy holy hill?
19½Ã 15:2 He who walks with integrity, and works righteousness, And speaks truth in his heart.
19½Ã 15:3 He does not slander with his tongue, Nor does evil to his neighbor, Nor takes up a reproach against his friend;
19½Ã 15:4 In whose eyes a reprobate is despised, But who honors those who fear the LORD; He swears to his own hurt, and does not change;
19½Ã 15:5 He does not put out his money at interest, Nor does he take a bribe against the innocent. He who does these things will never be shaken.
19½Ã 16:1 {A Mikhtam of David.} Preserve me, O God, for I take refuge in Thee.
19½Ã 16:2 I said to the LORD, "Thou art my Lord; I have no good besides Thee."
19½Ã 16:3 As for the saints who are in the earth, They are the majestic ones in whom is all my delight.
19½Ã 16:4 The sorrows of those who have bartered for another [god] will be multiplied; I shall not pour out their libations of blood, Nor shall I take their names upon my lips.
19½Ã 16:5 The LORD is the portion of my inheritance and my cup; Thou dost support my lot.
19½Ã 16:6 The lines have fallen to me in pleasant places; Indeed, my heritage is beautiful to me.
19½Ã 16:7 I will bless the LORD who has counseled me; Indeed, my mind instructs me in the night.
19½Ã 16:8 I have set the LORD continually before me; Because He is at my right hand, I will not be shaken.
19½Ã 16:9 Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory rejoices; My flesh also will dwell securely.
19½Ã 16:10 For Thou wilt not abandon my soul to Sheol; Neither wilt Thou allow Thy Holy One to undergo decay.
19½Ã 16:11 Thou wilt make known to me the path of life; In Thy presence is fulness of joy; In Thy right hand there are pleasures forever.
19½Ã 17:1 {A Prayer of David.} Hear a just cause, O LORD, give heed to my cry; Give ear to my prayer, which is not from deceitful lips.
19½Ã 17:2 Let my judgment come forth from Thy presence; Let Thine eyes look with equity.
19½Ã 17:3 Thou hast tried my heart; Thou hast visited [me] by night; Thou hast tested me and dost find nothing; I have purposed that my mouth will not transgress.
19½Ã 17:4 As for the deeds of men, by the word of Thy lips I have kept from the paths of the violent.
19½Ã 17:5 My steps have held fast to Thy paths. My feet have not slipped.
19½Ã 17:6 I have called upon Thee, for Thou wilt answer me, O God; Incline Thine ear to me, hear my speech.
19½Ã 17:7 Wondrously show Thy lovingkindness, O Savior of those who take refuge at Thy right hand From those who rise up [against them].
19½Ã 17:8 Keep me as the apple of the eye; Hide me in the shadow of Thy wings,
19½Ã 17:9 From the wicked who despoil me, My deadly enemies, who surround me.
19½Ã 17:10 They have closed their unfeeling [heart]; With their mouth they speak proudly.
19½Ã 17:11 They have now surrounded us in our steps; They set their eyes to cast [us] down to the ground.
19½Ã 17:12 He is like a lion that is eager to tear, And as a young lion lurking in hiding places.
