19½Ã 18:1 {For the choir director. [A Psalm] of David the servant of the LORD, who} (spoke to the LORD the words of this song in the day that the LORD) (delivered him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul. And) (he said,) "I love Thee, O LORD, my strength."
19½Ã 18:2 The LORD is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer, My God, my rock, in whom I take refuge; My shield and the horn of my salvation, my stronghold.
19½Ã 18:3 I call upon the LORD, who is worthy to be praised, And I am saved from my enemies.
19½Ã 18:4 The cords of death encompassed me, And the torrents of ungodliness terrified me.
19½Ã 18:5 The cords of Sheol surrounded me; The snares of death confronted me.
19½Ã 18:6 In my distress I called upon the LORD, And cried to my God for help; He heard my voice out of His temple, And my cry for help before Him came into His ears.
19½Ã 18:7 Then the earth shook and quaked; And the foundations of the mountains were trembling And were shaken, because He was angry.
19½Ã 18:8 Smoke went up out of His nostrils, And fire from His mouth devoured; Coals were kindled by it.
19½Ã 18:9 He bowed the heavens also, and came down With thick darkness under His feet.
19½Ã 18:10 And He rode upon a cherub and flew; And He sped upon the wings of the wind.
19½Ã 18:11 He made darkness His hiding place, His canopy around Him, Darkness of waters, thick clouds of the skies.
19½Ã 18:12 From the brightness before Him passed His thick clouds, Hailstones and coals of fire.
19½Ã 18:13 The LORD also thundered in the heavens, And the Most High uttered His voice, Hailstones and coals of fire.
19½Ã 18:14 And He sent out His arrows, and scattered them, And lightning flashes in abundance, and routed them.
19½Ã 18:15 Then the channels of water appeared, And the foundations of the world were laid bare At Thy rebuke, O LORD, At the blast of the breath of Thy nostrils.
19½Ã 18:16 He sent from on high, He took me; He drew me out of many waters.
19½Ã 18:17 He delivered me from my strong enemy, And from those who hated me, for they were too mighty for me.
