19½Ã 18:19 He brought me forth also into a broad place; He rescued me, because He delighted in me.
19½Ã 18:20 The LORD has rewarded me according to my righteousness; According to the cleanness of my hands He has recompensed me.
19½Ã 18:21 For I have kept the ways of the LORD, And have not wickedly departed from my God.
19½Ã 18:22 For all His ordinances were before me, And I did not put away His statutes from me.
19½Ã 18:23 I was also blameless with Him, And I kept myself from my iniquity.
19½Ã 18:24 Therefore the LORD has recompensed me according to my righteousness, According to the cleanness of my hands in His eyes.
19½Ã 18:25 With the kind Thou dost show Thyself kind; With the blameless Thou dost show Thyself blameless;
19½Ã 18:26 With the pure Thou dost show Thyself pure; And with the crooked Thou dost show Thyself astute.
19½Ã 18:27 For Thou dost save an afflicted people; But haughty eyes Thou dost abase.
19½Ã 18:28 For Thou dost light my lamp; The LORD my God illumines my darkness.
19½Ã 18:29 For by Thee I can run upon a troop; And by my God I can leap over a wall.
19½Ã 18:30 As for God, His way is blameless; The word of the LORD is tried; He is a shield to all who take refuge in Him.
19½Ã 18:31 For who is God, but the LORD? And who is a rock, except our God,
19½Ã 18:32 The God who girds me with strength, And makes my way blameless?
19½Ã 18:33 He makes my feet like hinds' [feet], And sets me upon my high places.
19½Ã 18:34 He trains my hands for battle, So that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.
19½Ã 18:35 Thou hast also given me the shield of Thy salvation, And Thy right hand upholds me; And Thy gentleness makes me great.
19½Ã 18:36 Thou dost enlarge my steps under me, And my feet have not slipped.
19½Ã 18:37 I pursued my enemies and overtook them, And I did not turn back until they were consumed.
19½Ã 18:38 I shattered them, so that they were not able to rise; They fell under my feet.
19½Ã 18:39 For Thou hast girded me with strength for battle; Thou hast subdued under me those who rose up against me.
19½Ã 18:40 Thou hast also made my enemies turn their backs to me, And I destroyed those who hated me.
19½Ã 18:41 They cried for help, but there was none to save, [Even] to the LORD, but He did not answer them.
19½Ã 18:42 Then I beat them fine as the dust before the wind; I emptied them out as the mire of the streets.
19½Ã 18:43 Thou hast delivered me from the contentions of the people; Thou hast placed me as head of the nations; A people whom I have not known serve me.
19½Ã 18:44 As soon as they hear, they obey me; Foreigners submit to me.
19½Ã 18:45 Foreigners fade away, And come trembling out of their fortresses.
19½Ã 18:46 The LORD lives, and blessed be my rock; And exalted be the God of my salvation,
19½Ã 18:47 The God who executes vengeance for me, And subdues peoples under me.
19½Ã 18:48 He delivers me from my enemies; Surely Thou dost lift me above those who rise up against me; Thou dost rescue me from the violent man.
19½Ã 18:49 Therefore I will give thanks to Thee among the nations, O LORD, And I will sing praises to Thy name.
19½Ã 18:50 He gives great deliverance to His king, And shows lovingkindness to His anointed, To David and his descendants forever.
19½Ã 19:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} The heavens are telling of the glory of God; And their expanse is declaring the work of His hands.
19½Ã 19:2 Day to day pours forth speech, And night to night reveals knowledge.
