19½Ã 22:14 I am poured out like water, And all my bones are out of joint; My heart is like wax; It is melted within me.
19½Ã 22:15 My strength is dried up like a potsherd, And my tongue cleaves to my jaws; And Thou dost lay me in the dust of death.
19½Ã 22:16 For dogs have surrounded me; A band of evildoers has encompassed me; They pierced my hands and my feet.
19½Ã 22:17 I can count all my bones. They look, they stare at me;
19½Ã 22:18 They divide my garments among them, And for my clothing they cast lots.
19½Ã 22:19 But Thou, O LORD, be not far off; O Thou my help, hasten to my assistance.
19½Ã 22:20 Deliver my soul from the sword, My only [life] from the power of the dog.
19½Ã 22:21 Save me from the lion's mouth; And from the horns of the wild oxen Thou dost answer me.
19½Ã 22:22 I will tell of Thy name to my brethren; In the midst of the assembly I will praise Thee.
19½Ã 22:23 You who fear the LORD, praise Him; All you descendants of Jacob, glorify Him, And stand in awe of Him, all you descendants of Israel.
19½Ã 22:24 For He has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted; Neither has He hidden His face from him; But when he cried to Him for help, He heard.
19½Ã 22:25 From Thee [comes] my praise in the great assembly; I shall pay my vows before those who fear Him.
19½Ã 22:26 The afflicted shall eat and be satisfied; Those who seek Him will praise the LORD. Let your heart live forever!
19½Ã 22:27 All the ends of the earth will remember and turn to the LORD, And all the families of the nations will worship before Thee.
19½Ã 22:28 For the kingdom is the Lord's, And He rules over the nations.
19½Ã 22:29 All the prosperous of the earth will eat and worship, All those who go down to the dust will bow before Him, Even he who cannot keep his soul alive.
19½Ã 22:30 Posterity will serve Him; It will be told of the LORD to the [coming] generation.
19½Ã 22:31 They will come and will declare His righteousness To a people who will be born, that He has performed [it.]
19½Ã 23:1 {A Psalm of David.} The LORD is my shepherd, I shall not want.
19½Ã 23:2 He makes me lie down in green pastures; He leads me beside quiet waters.
19½Ã 23:3 He restores my soul; He guides me in the paths of righteousness For His name's sake.
19½Ã 23:4 Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I fear no evil; for Thou art with me; Thy rod and Thy staff, they comfort me.
19½Ã 23:5 Thou dost prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies; Thou hast anointed my head with oil; My cup overflows.
19½Ã 23:6 Surely goodness and lovingkindness will follow me all the days of my life, And I will dwell in the house of the LORD forever.
19½Ã 24:1 {A Psalm of David.} The earth is the Lord's, and all it contains, The world, and those who dwell in it.
19½Ã 24:2 For He has founded it upon the seas, And established it upon the rivers.
19½Ã 24:3 Who may ascend into the hill of the LORD? And who may stand in His holy place?
19½Ã 24:4 He who has clean hands and a pure heart, Who has not lifted up his soul to falsehood, And has not sworn deceitfully.
19½Ã 24:5 He shall receive a blessing from the LORD And righteousness from the God of his salvation.
19½Ã 24:6 This is the generation of those who seek Him, Who seek Thy face-- [ even] Jacob. Selah.
19½Ã 24:7 Lift up your heads, O gates, And be lifted up, O ancient doors, That the King of glory may come in!
19½Ã 24:8 Who is the King of glory? The LORD strong and mighty, The LORD mighty in battle.
19½Ã 24:9 Lift up your heads, O gates, And lift [them] up, O ancient doors, That the King of glory may come in!
19½Ã 24:10 Who is this King of glory? The LORD of hosts, He is the King of glory. Selah.
19½Ã 25:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} To Thee, O LORD, I lift up my soul.
19½Ã 25:2 O my God, in Thee I trust, Do not let me be ashamed; Do not let my enemies exult over me.
19½Ã 25:3 Indeed, none of those who wait for Thee will be ashamed; Those who deal treacherously without cause will be ashamed.
19½Ã 25:4 Make me know Thy ways, O LORD; Teach me Thy paths.
19½Ã 25:5 Lead me in Thy truth and teach me, For Thou art the God of my salvation; For Thee I wait all the day.
19½Ã 25:6 Remember, O LORD, Thy compassion and Thy lovingkindnesses, For they have been from of old.
19½Ã 25:7 Do not remember the sins of my youth or my transgressions; According to Thy lovingkindness remember Thou me, For Thy goodness' sake, O LORD.
19½Ã 25:8 Good and upright is the LORD; Therefore He instructs sinners in the way.
19½Ã 25:9 He leads the humble in justice, And He teaches the humble His way.
19½Ã 25:10 All the paths of the LORD are lovingkindness and truth To those who keep His covenant and His testimonies.
19½Ã 25:11 For Thy name's sake, O LORD, Pardon my iniquity, for it is great.
19½Ã 25:12 Who is the man who fears the LORD? He will instruct him in the way he should choose.
19½Ã 25:13 His soul will abide in prosperity, And his descendants will inherit the land.
19½Ã 25:14 The secret of the LORD is for those who fear Him, And He will make them know His covenant.
19½Ã 25:15 My eyes are continually toward the LORD, For He will pluck my feet out of the net.
19½Ã 25:16 Turn to me and be gracious to me, For I am lonely and afflicted.
19½Ã 25:17 The troubles of my heart are enlarged; Bring me out of my distresses.
19½Ã 25:18 Look upon my affliction and my trouble, And forgive all my sins.
19½Ã 25:19 Look upon my enemies, for they are many; And they hate me with violent hatred.
19½Ã 25:20 Guard my soul and deliver me; Do not let me be ashamed, for I take refuge in Thee.
19½Ã 25:21 Let integrity and uprightness preserve me, For I wait for Thee.
19½Ã 25:22 Redeem Israel, O God, Out of all his troubles.
19½Ã 26:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} Vindicate me, O LORD, for I have walked in my integrity; And I have trusted in the LORD without wavering.
19½Ã 26:2 Examine me, O LORD, and try me; Test my mind and my heart.
19½Ã 26:3 For Thy lovingkindness is before my eyes, And I have walked in Thy truth.
19½Ã 26:4 I do not sit with deceitful men, Nor will I go with pretenders.
19½Ã 26:5 I hate the assembly of evildoers, And I will not sit with the wicked.
19½Ã 26:6 I shall wash my hands in innocence, And I will go about Thine altar, O LORD,
19½Ã 26:7 That I may proclaim with the voice of thanksgiving, And declare all Thy wonders.
19½Ã 26:8 O LORD, I love the habitation of Thy house, And the place where Thy glory dwells.
19½Ã 26:9 Do not take my soul away [along] with sinners, Nor my life with men of bloodshed,
19½Ã 26:10 In whose hands is a wicked scheme, And whose right hand is full of bribes.
19½Ã 26:11 But as for me, I shall walk in my integrity; Redeem me, and be gracious to me.
19½Ã 26:12 My foot stands on a level place; In the congregations I shall bless the LORD.
19½Ã 27:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} The LORD is my light and my salvation; Whom shall I fear? The LORD is the defense of my life; Whom shall I dread?
19½Ã 27:2 When evildoers came upon me to devour my flesh, My adversaries and my enemies, they stumbled and fell.
19½Ã 27:3 Though a host encamp against me, My heart will not fear; Though war arise against me, In [spite of] this I shall be confident.
19½Ã 27:4 One thing I have asked from the LORD, that I shall seek£º That I may dwell in the house of the LORD all the days of my life, To behold the beauty of the LORD, And to meditate in His temple.
19½Ã 27:5 For in the day of trouble He will conceal me in His tabernacle; In the secret place of His tent He will hide me; He will lift me up on a rock.
19½Ã 27:6 And now my head will be lifted up above my enemies around me; And I will offer in His tent sacrifices with shouts of joy; I will sing, yes, I will sing praises to the LORD.
19½Ã 27:7 Hear, O LORD, when I cry with my voice, And be gracious to me and answer me.
19½Ã 27:8 [When Thou didst say,] "Seek My face," my heart said to Thee, "Thy face, O LORD, I shall seek."
19½Ã 27:9 Do not hide Thy face from me, Do not turn Thy servant away in anger; Thou hast been my help; Do not abandon me nor forsake me, O God of my salvation!
19½Ã 27:10 For my father and my mother have forsaken me, But the LORD will take me up.
19½Ã 27:11 Teach me Thy way, O LORD, And lead me in a level path, Because of my foes.
19½Ã 27:12 Do not deliver me over to the desire of my adversaries; For false witnesses have risen against me, And such as breathe out violence.
19½Ã 27:13 [I would have despaired] unless I had believed that I would see the goodness of the LORD In the land of the living.
19½Ã 27:14 Wait for the LORD; Be strong, and let your heart take courage; Yes, wait for the LORD.
19½Ã 28:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} To Thee, O LORD, I call; My rock, do not be deaf to me, Lest, if Thou be silent to me, I become like those who go down to the pit.
19½Ã 28:2 Hear the voice of my supplications when I cry to Thee for help, When I lift up my hands toward Thy holy sanctuary.
19½Ã 28:3 Do not drag me away with the wicked And with those who work iniquity; Who speak peace with their neighbors, While evil is in their hearts.
19½Ã 28:4 Requite them according to their work and according to the evil of their practices; Requite them according to the deeds of their hands; Repay them their recompense.
19½Ã 28:5 Because they do not regard the works of the LORD Nor the deeds of His hands, He will tear them down and not build them up.
19½Ã 28:6 Blessed be the LORD, Because He has heard the voice of my supplication.
19½Ã 28:7 The LORD is my strength and my shield; My heart trusts in Him, and I am helped; Therefore my heart exults, And with my song I shall thank Him.
19½Ã 28:8 The LORD is their strength, And He is a saving defense to His anointed.
19½Ã 28:9 Save Thy people, and bless Thine inheritance; Be their shepherd also, and carry them forever.
19½Ã 29:1 {A Psalm of David.} Ascribe to the LORD, O sons of the mighty, Ascribe to the LORD glory and strength.
19½Ã 29:2 Ascribe to the LORD the glory due to His name; Worship the LORD in holy array.
19½Ã 29:3 The voice of the LORD is upon the waters; The God of glory thunders, The LORD is over many waters.
19½Ã 29:4 The voice of the LORD is powerful, The voice of the LORD is majestic.
19½Ã 29:5 The voice of the LORD breaks the cedars; Yes, the LORD breaks in pieces the cedars of Lebanon.
19½Ã 29:6 And He makes Lebanon skip like a calf, And Sirion like a young wild ox.
19½Ã 29:7 The voice of the LORD hews out flames of fire.
19½Ã 29:8 The voice of the LORD shakes the wilderness; The LORD shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.
19½Ã 29:9 The voice of the LORD makes the deer to calve, And strips the forests bare, And in His temple everything says, "Glory!"
19½Ã 29:10 The LORD sat [as King] at the flood; Yes, the LORD sits as King forever.
19½Ã 29:11 The LORD will give strength to His people; The LORD will bless His people with peace.
19½Ã 30:1 {A Psalm; a Song at the Dedication of the House. [A Psalm] of David.} I will extol Thee, O LORD, for Thou hast lifted me up, And hast not let my enemies rejoice over me.
19½Ã 30:2 O LORD my God, I cried to Thee for help, and Thou didst heal me.
19½Ã 30:3 O LORD, Thou hast brought up my soul from Sheol; Thou hast kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.
19½Ã 30:4 Sing praise to the LORD, you His godly ones, And give thanks to His holy name.
19½Ã 30:5 For His anger is but for a moment, His favor is for a lifetime; Weeping may last for the night, But a shout of joy [comes] in the morning.
19½Ã 30:6 Now as for me, I said in my prosperity, "I will never be moved."
19½Ã 30:7 O LORD, by Thy favor Thou hast made my mountain to stand strong; Thou didst hide Thy face, I was dismayed.
19½Ã 30:8 To Thee, O LORD, I called, And to the Lord I made supplication£º
19½Ã 30:9 "What profit is there in my blood, if I go down to the pit? Will the dust praise Thee? Will it declare Thy faithfulness?
19½Ã 30:10 "Hear, O LORD, and be gracious to me; O LORD, be Thou my helper."
19½Ã 30:11 Thou hast turned for me my mourning into dancing; Thou hast loosed my sackcloth and girded me with gladness;
19½Ã 30:12 That [my] soul may sing praise to Thee, and not be silent. O LORD my God, I will give thanks to Thee forever.
19½Ã 31:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} In Thee, O LORD, I have taken refuge; Let me never be ashamed; In Thy righteousness deliver me.
19½Ã 31:2 Incline Thine ear to me, rescue me quickly; Be Thou to me a rock of strength, A stronghold to save me.
19½Ã 31:3 For Thou art my rock and my fortress; For Thy name's sake Thou wilt lead me and guide me.
19½Ã 31:4 Thou wilt pull me out of the net which they have secretly laid for me; For Thou art my strength.
19½Ã 31:5 Into Thy hand I commit my spirit; Thou hast ransomed me, O LORD, God of truth.
19½Ã 31:6 I hate those who regard vain idols; But I trust in the LORD.
19½Ã 31:7 I will rejoice and be glad in Thy lovingkindness, Because Thou hast seen my affliction; Thou hast known the troubles of my soul,
19½Ã 31:8 And Thou hast not given me over into the hand of the enemy; Thou hast set my feet in a large place.
19½Ã 31:9 Be gracious to me, O LORD, for I am in distress; My eye is wasted away from grief, my soul and my body [also.]
19½Ã 31:10 For my life is spent with sorrow, And my years with sighing; My strength has failed because of my iniquity, And my body has wasted away.
19½Ã 31:11 Because of all my adversaries, I have become a reproach, Especially to my neighbors, And an object of dread to my acquaintances; Those who see me in the street flee from me.
19½Ã 31:12 I am forgotten as a dead man, out of mind, I am like a broken vessel.
19½Ã 31:13 For I have heard the slander of many, Terror is on every side; While they took counsel together against me, They schemed to take away my life.
19½Ã 31:14 But as for me, I trust in Thee, O LORD, I say, "Thou art my God."
19½Ã 31:15 My times are in Thy hand; Deliver me from the hand of my enemies, and from those who persecute me.
19½Ã 31:16 Make Thy face to shine upon Thy servant; Save me in Thy lovingkindness.
19½Ã 31:17 Let me not be put to shame, O LORD, for I call upon Thee; Let the wicked be put to shame, let them be silent in Sheol.
19½Ã 31:18 Let the lying lips be dumb, Which speak arrogantly against the righteous With pride and contempt.
19½Ã 31:19 How great is Thy goodness, Which Thou hast stored up for those who fear Thee, Which Thou hast wrought for those who take refuge in Thee, Before the sons of men!
19½Ã 31:20 Thou dost hide them in the secret place of Thy presence from the conspiracies of man; Thou dost keep them secretly in a shelter from the strife of tongues.
19½Ã 31:21 Blessed be the LORD, For He has made marvelous His lovingkindness to me in a besieged city.
19½Ã 31:22 As for me, I said in my alarm, "I am cut off from before Thine eyes"; Nevertheless Thou didst hear the voice of my supplications When I cried to Thee.
19½Ã 31:23 O love the LORD, all you His godly ones! The LORD preserves the faithful, And fully recompenses the proud doer.
19½Ã 31:24 Be strong, and let your heart take courage, All you who hope in the LORD.
19½Ã 32:1 {[A Psalm] of David. A Maskil.} How blessed is he whose transgression is forgiven, Whose sin is covered!
19½Ã 32:2 How blessed is the man to whom the LORD does not impute iniquity, And in whose spirit there is no deceit!
19½Ã 32:3 When I kept silent [about my sin], my body wasted away Through my groaning all day long.
19½Ã 32:4 For day and night Thy hand was heavy upon me; My vitality was drained away [as] with the fever heat of summer. Selah.
19½Ã 32:5 I acknowledged my sin to Thee, And my iniquity I did not hide; I said, "I will confess my transgressions to the LORD"; And Thou didst forgive the guilt of my sin. Selah.
19½Ã 32:6 Therefore, let everyone who is godly pray to Thee in a time when Thou mayest be found; Surely in a flood of great waters they shall not reach him.
19½Ã 32:7 Thou art my hiding place; Thou dost preserve me from trouble; Thou dost surround me with songs of deliverance. Selah.
19½Ã 32:8 I will instruct you and teach you in the way which you should go; I will counsel you with My eye upon you.
19½Ã 32:9 Do not be as the horse or as the mule which have no understanding, Whose trappings include bit and bridle to hold them in check, [Otherwise] they will not come near to you.
19½Ã 32:10 Many are the sorrows of the wicked; But he who trusts in the LORD, lovingkindness shall surround him.
19½Ã 32:11 Be glad in the LORD and rejoice, you righteous ones, And shout for joy, all you who are upright in heart.
19½Ã 33:1 Sing for joy in the LORD, O you righteous ones; Praise is becoming to the upright.
19½Ã 33:2 Give thanks to the LORD with the lyre; Sing praises to Him with a harp of ten strings.
19½Ã 33:3 Sing to Him a new song; Play skillfully with a shout of joy.
19½Ã 33:4 For the word of the LORD is upright; And all His work is [done] in faithfulness.
19½Ã 33:5 He loves righteousness and justice; The earth is full of the lovingkindness of the LORD.
19½Ã 33:6 By the word of the LORD the heavens were made, And by the breath of His mouth all their host.
19½Ã 33:7 He gathers the waters of the sea together as a heap; He lays up the deeps in storehouses.
19½Ã 33:8 Let all the earth fear the LORD; Let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of Him.
19½Ã 33:9 For He spoke, and it was done; He commanded, and it stood fast.
19½Ã 33:10 The LORD nullifies the counsel of the nations; He frustrates the plans of the peoples.
19½Ã 33:11 The counsel of the LORD stands forever, The plans of His heart from generation to generation.
19½Ã 33:12 Blessed is the nation whose God is the LORD, The people whom He has chosen for His own inheritance.
19½Ã 33:13 The LORD looks from heaven; He sees all the sons of men;
19½Ã 33:14 From His dwelling place He looks out On all the inhabitants of the earth,
19½Ã 33:15 He who fashions the hearts of them all, He who understands all their works.
19½Ã 33:16 The king is not saved by a mighty army; A warrior is not delivered by great strength.
19½Ã 33:17 A horse is a false hope for victory; Nor does it deliver anyone by its great strength.
19½Ã 33:18 Behold, the eye of the LORD is on those who fear Him, On those who hope for His lovingkindness,
19½Ã 33:19 To deliver their soul from death, And to keep them alive in famine.
19½Ã 33:20 Our soul waits for the LORD; He is our help and our shield.
19½Ã 33:21 For our heart rejoices in Him, Because we trust in His holy name.
19½Ã 33:22 Let Thy lovingkindness, O LORD, be upon us, According as we have hoped in Thee.
19½Ã 34:1 {[A Psalm] of David when he feigned madness before Abimelech, who drove him} (away and he departed.) I will bless the LORD at all times; His praise shall continually be in my mouth.
19½Ã 34:2 My soul shall make its boast in the LORD; The humble shall hear it and rejoice.
19½Ã 34:3 O magnify the LORD with me, And let us exalt His name together.
19½Ã 34:4 I sought the LORD, and He answered me, And delivered me from all my fears.
19½Ã 34:5 They looked to Him and were radiant, And their faces shall never be ashamed.
19½Ã 34:6 This poor man cried and the LORD heard him, And saved him out of all his troubles.
19½Ã 34:7 The angel of the LORD encamps around those who fear Him, And rescues them.
19½Ã 34:8 O taste and see that the LORD is good; How blessed is the man who takes refuge in Him!
19½Ã 34:9 O fear the LORD, you His saints; For to those who fear Him, there is no want.
19½Ã 34:10 The young lions do lack and suffer hunger; But they who seek the LORD shall not be in want of any good thing.
19½Ã 34:11 Come, you children, listen to me; I will teach you the fear of the LORD.
19½Ã 34:12 Who is the man who desires life, And loves [length of] days that he may see good?
19½Ã 34:13 Keep your tongue from evil, And your lips from speaking deceit.
19½Ã 34:14 Depart from evil, and do good; Seek peace, and pursue it.
19½Ã 34:15 The eyes of the LORD are toward the righteous, And His ears are [open] to their cry.
19½Ã 34:16 The face of the LORD is against evildoers, To cut off the memory of them from the earth.
19½Ã 34:17 [The righteous] cry and the LORD hears, And delivers them out of all their troubles.
19½Ã 34:18 The LORD is near to the brokenhearted, And saves those who are crushed in spirit.
19½Ã 34:19 Many are the afflictions of the righteous; But the LORD delivers him out of them all.
19½Ã 34:20 He keeps all his bones; Not one of them is broken.
19½Ã 34:21 Evil shall slay the wicked; And those who hate the righteous will be condemned.
19½Ã 34:22 The LORD redeems the soul of His servants; And none of those who take refuge in Him will be condemned.
19½Ã 35:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} Contend, O LORD, with those who contend with me; Fight against those who fight against me.
19½Ã 35:2 Take hold of buckler and shield, And rise up for my help.
19½Ã 35:3 Draw also the spear and the battle-axe to meet those who pursue me; Say to my soul, "I am your salvation."
19½Ã 35:4 Let those be ashamed and dishonored who seek my life; Let those be turned back and humiliated who devise evil against me.
19½Ã 35:5 Let them be like chaff before the wind, With the angel of the LORD driving [them] on.
19½Ã 35:6 Let their way be dark and slippery, With the angel of the LORD pursuing them.
19½Ã 35:7 For without cause they hid their net for me; Without cause they dug a pit for my soul.
19½Ã 35:8 Let destruction come upon him unawares; And let the net which he hid catch himself; Into that very destruction let him fall.
19½Ã 35:9 And my soul shall rejoice in the LORD; It shall exult in His salvation.
19½Ã 35:10 All my bones will say, "LORD, who is like Thee, Who delivers the afflicted from him who is too strong for him, And the afflicted and the needy from him who robs him?"
19½Ã 35:11 Malicious witnesses rise up; They ask me of things that I do not know.
19½Ã 35:12 They repay me evil for good, [To] the bereavement of my soul.
19½Ã 35:13 But as for me, when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth; I humbled my soul with fasting; And my prayer kept returning to my bosom.
19½Ã 35:14 I went about as though it were my friend or brother; I bowed down mourning, as one who sorrows for a mother.
19½Ã 35:15 But at my stumbling they rejoiced, and gathered themselves together; The smiters whom I did not know gathered together against me, They slandered me without ceasing.
19½Ã 35:16 Like godless jesters at a feast, They gnashed at me with their teeth.
19½Ã 35:17 Lord, how long wilt Thou look on? Rescue my soul from their ravages, My only [life] from the lions.
19½Ã 35:18 I will give Thee thanks in the great congregation; I will praise Thee among a mighty throng.
19½Ã 35:19 Do not let those who are wrongfully my enemies rejoice over me; Neither let those who hate me without cause wink maliciously.
19½Ã 35:20 For they do not speak peace, But they devise deceitful words against those who are quiet in the land.
19½Ã 35:21 And they opened their mouth wide against me; They said, "Aha, aha, our eyes have seen it!"
19½Ã 35:22 Thou hast seen it, O LORD, do not keep silent; O Lord, do not be far from me.
19½Ã 35:23 Stir up Thyself, and awake to my right, And to my cause, my God and my Lord.
19½Ã 35:24 Judge me, O LORD my God, according to Thy righteousness; And do not let them rejoice over me.
19½Ã 35:25 Do not let them say in their heart, "Aha, our desire!" Do not let them say, "We have swallowed him up!"
19½Ã 35:26 Let those be ashamed and humiliated altogether who rejoice at my distress; Let those be clothed with shame and dishonor who magnify themselves over me.
19½Ã 35:27 Let them shout for joy and rejoice, who favor my vindication; And let them say continually, "The LORD be magnified, Who delights in the prosperity of His servant."
19½Ã 35:28 And my tongue shall declare Thy righteousness [And] Thy praise all day long.
19½Ã 36:1 {For the choir director. [A Psalm] of David the servant of the LORD.} Transgression speaks to the ungodly within his heart; There is no fear of God before his eyes.
19½Ã 36:2 For it flatters him in his [own] eyes, Concerning the discovery of his iniquity [and] the hatred [of it.]
19½Ã 36:3 The words of his mouth are wickedness and deceit; He has ceased to be wise [and] to do good.
19½Ã 36:4 He plans wickedness upon his bed; He sets himself on a path that is not good; He does not despise evil.
19½Ã 36:5 Thy lovingkindness, O LORD, extends to the heavens, Thy faithfulness [reaches] to the skies.
19½Ã 36:6 Thy righteousness is like the mountains of God; Thy judgments are [ like] a great deep. O LORD, Thou preservest man and beast.
19½Ã 36:7 How precious is Thy lovingkindness, O God! And the children of men take refuge in the shadow of Thy wings.
19½Ã 36:8 They drink their fill of the abundance of Thy house; And Thou dost give them to drink of the river of Thy delights.
19½Ã 36:9 For with Thee is the fountain of life; In Thy light we see light.
19½Ã 36:10 O continue Thy lovingkindness to those who know Thee, And Thy righteousness to the upright in heart.
19½Ã 36:11 Let not the foot of pride come upon me, And let not the hand of the wicked drive me away.
19½Ã 36:12 There the doers of iniquity have fallen; They have been thrust down and cannot rise.
19½Ã 37:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} Do not fret because of evildoers, Be not envious toward wrongdoers.
19½Ã 37:2 For they will wither quickly like the grass, And fade like the green herb.
19½Ã 37:3 Trust in the LORD, and do good; Dwell in the land and cultivate faithfulness.
19½Ã 37:4 Delight yourself in the LORD; And He will give you the desires of your heart.
19½Ã 37:5 Commit your way to the LORD, Trust also in Him, and He will do it.
19½Ã 37:6 And He will bring forth your righteousness as the light, And your judgment as the noonday.
19½Ã 37:7 Rest in the LORD and wait patiently for Him; Do not fret because of him who prospers in his way, Because of the man who carries out wicked schemes.
19½Ã 37:8 Cease from anger, and forsake wrath; Do not fret, [it leads] only to evildoing.
19½Ã 37:9 For evildoers will be cut off, But those who wait for the LORD, they will inherit the land.
19½Ã 37:10 Yet a little while and the wicked man will be no more; And you will look carefully for his place, and he will not be [there.]
19½Ã 37:11 But the humble will inherit the land, And will delight themselves in abundant prosperity.
19½Ã 37:12 The wicked plots against the righteous, And gnashes at him with his teeth.
19½Ã 37:13 The Lord laughs at him; For He sees his day is coming.
19½Ã 37:14 The wicked have drawn the sword and bent their bow, To cast down the afflicted and the needy, To slay those who are upright in conduct.
19½Ã 37:15 Their sword will enter their own heart, And their bows will be broken.
19½Ã 37:16 Better is the little of the righteous Than the abundance of many wicked.
19½Ã 37:17 For the arms of the wicked will be broken; But the LORD sustains the righteous.
19½Ã 37:18 The LORD knows the days of the blameless; And their inheritance will be forever.
19½Ã 37:19 They will not be ashamed in the time of evil; And in the days of famine they will have abundance.
19½Ã 37:20 But the wicked will perish; And the enemies of the LORD will be like the glory of the pastures, They vanish-- like smoke they vanish away.
19½Ã 37:21 The wicked borrows and does not pay back, But the righteous is gracious and gives.
19½Ã 37:22 For those blessed by Him will inherit the land; But those cursed by Him will be cut off.
19½Ã 37:23 The steps of a man are established by the LORD; And He delights in his way.
19½Ã 37:24 When he falls, he shall not be hurled headlong; Because the LORD is the One who holds his hand.
19½Ã 37:25 I have been young, and now I am old; Yet I have not seen the righteous forsaken, Or his descendants begging bread.
19½Ã 37:26 All day long he is gracious and lends; And his descendants are a blessing.
19½Ã 37:27 Depart from evil, and do good, So you will abide forever.
19½Ã 37:28 For the LORD loves justice, And does not forsake His godly ones; They are preserved forever; But the descendants of the wicked will be cut off.
19½Ã 37:29 The righteous will inherit the land, And dwell in it forever.
19½Ã 37:30 The mouth of the righteous utters wisdom, And his tongue speaks justice.
19½Ã 37:31 The law of his God is in his heart; His steps do not slip.
19½Ã 37:32 The wicked spies upon the righteous, And seeks to kill him.
19½Ã 37:33 The LORD will not leave him in his hand, Or let him be condemned when he is judged.
