19½Ã 37:35 I have seen a violent, wicked man Spreading himself like a luxuriant tree in its native soil.
19½Ã 37:36 Then he passed away, and lo, he was no more; I sought for him, but he could not be found.
19½Ã 37:37 Mark the blameless man, and behold the upright; For the man of peace will have a posterity.
19½Ã 37:38 But transgressors will be altogether destroyed; The posterity of the wicked will be cut off.
19½Ã 37:39 But the salvation of the righteous is from the LORD; He is their strength in time of trouble.
19½Ã 37:40 And the LORD helps them, and delivers them; He delivers them from the wicked, and saves them, Because they take refuge in Him.
19½Ã 38:1 {A Psalm of David, for a memorial.} O LORD, rebuke me not in Thy wrath; And chasten me not in Thy burning anger.
19½Ã 38:2 For Thine arrows have sunk deep into me, And Thy hand has pressed down on me.
19½Ã 38:3 There is no soundness in my flesh because of Thine indignation; There is no health in my bones because of my sin.
19½Ã 38:4 For my iniquities are gone over my head; As a heavy burden they weigh too much for me.
19½Ã 38:5 My wounds grow foul [and] fester. Because of my folly,
19½Ã 38:6 I am bent over and greatly bowed down; I go mourning all day long.
19½Ã 38:7 For my loins are filled with burning; And there is no soundness in my flesh.
19½Ã 38:8 I am benumbed and badly crushed; I groan because of the agitation of my heart.
19½Ã 38:9 Lord, all my desire is before Thee; And my sighing is not hidden from Thee.
19½Ã 38:10 My heart throbs, my strength fails me; And the light of my eyes, even that has gone from me.
19½Ã 38:11 My loved ones and my friends stand aloof from my plague; And my kinsmen stand afar off.
19½Ã 38:12 Those who seek my life lay snares [for me]; And those who seek to injure me have threatened destruction, And they devise treachery all day long.
19½Ã 38:13 But I, like a deaf man, do not hear; And I am like a dumb man who does not open his mouth.
19½Ã 38:14 Yes, I am like a man who does not hear, And in whose mouth are no arguments.
19½Ã 38:15 For I hope in Thee, O LORD; Thou wilt answer, O Lord my God.
19½Ã 38:16 For I said, "May they not rejoice over me, [Who,] when my foot slips, would magnify themselves against me."
19½Ã 38:17 For I am ready to fall, And my sorrow is continually before me.
19½Ã 38:18 For I confess my iniquity; I am full of anxiety because of my sin.
19½Ã 38:19 But my enemies are vigorous [and] strong; And many are those who hate me wrongfully.
19½Ã 38:20 And those who repay evil for good, They oppose me, because I follow what is good.
19½Ã 38:21 Do not forsake me, O LORD; O my God, do not be far from me!
19½Ã 38:22 Make haste to help me, O Lord, my salvation!
19½Ã 39:1 {For the choir director, for Jeduthun. A Psalm of David.} I said, " I will guard my ways, That I may not sin with my tongue; I will guard my mouth as with a muzzle, While the wicked are in my presence. "
19½Ã 39:2 I was dumb and silent, I refrained [even] from good; And my sorrow grew worse.
19½Ã 39:3 My heart was hot within me; While I was musing the fire burned; [Then] I spoke with my tongue£º
19½Ã 39:4 "LORD, make me to know my end, And what is the extent of my days, Let me know how transient I am.
19½Ã 39:5 "Behold, Thou hast made my days [as] handbreadths, And my lifetime as nothing in Thy sight, Surely every man at his best is a mere breath. Selah.
19½Ã 39:6 "Surely every man walks about as a phantom; Surely they make an uproar for nothing; He amasses [riches], and does not know who will gather them.
19½Ã 39:7 "And now, Lord, for what do I wait? My hope is in Thee.
19½Ã 39:8 "Deliver me from all my transgressions; Make me not the reproach of the foolish.
19½Ã 39:9 "I have become dumb, I do not open my mouth, Because it is Thou who hast done [it.]
19½Ã 39:10 "Remove Thy plague from me; Because of the opposition of Thy hand, I am perishing.
19½Ã 39:11 "With reproofs Thou dost chasten a man for iniquity; Thou dost consume as a moth what is precious to him; Surely every man is a mere breath. Selah.
19½Ã 39:12 "Hear my prayer, O LORD, and give ear to my cry; Do not be silent at my tears; For I am a stranger with Thee, A sojourner like all my fathers.
19½Ã 39:13 "Turn Thy gaze away from me, that I may smile [again], Before I depart and am no more."
19½Ã 40:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} I waited patiently for the LORD; And He inclined to me, and heard my cry.
19½Ã 40:2 He brought me up out of the pit of destruction, out of the miry clay; And He set my feet upon a rock making my footsteps firm.
19½Ã 40:3 And He put a new song in my mouth, a song of praise to our God; Many will see and fear, And will trust in the LORD.
19½Ã 40:4 How blessed is the man who has made the LORD his trust, And has not turned to the proud, nor to those who lapse into falsehood.
19½Ã 40:5 Many, O LORD my God, are the wonders which Thou hast done, And Thy thoughts toward us; There is none to compare with Thee; If I would declare and speak of them, They would be too numerous to count.
19½Ã 40:6 Sacrifice and meal offering Thou hast not desired; My ears Thou hast opened; Burnt offering and sin offering Thou hast not required.
19½Ã 40:7 Then I said, "Behold, I come; In the scroll of the book it is written of me;
19½Ã 40:8 I delight to do Thy will, O my God; Thy Law is within my heart. "
19½Ã 40:9 I have proclaimed glad tidings of righteousness in the great congregation; Behold, I will not restrain my lips, O LORD, Thou knowest.
19½Ã 40:10 I have not hidden Thy righteousness within my heart; I have spoken of Thy faithfulness and Thy salvation; I have not concealed Thy lovingkindness and Thy truth from the great congregation.
19½Ã 40:11 Thou, O LORD, wilt not withhold Thy compassion from me; Thy lovingkindness and Thy truth will continually preserve me.
19½Ã 40:12 For evils beyond number have surrounded me; My iniquities have overtaken me, so that I am not able to see; They are more numerous than the hairs of my head; And my heart has failed me.
19½Ã 40:13 Be pleased, O LORD, to deliver me; Make haste, O LORD, to help me.
19½Ã 40:14 Let those be ashamed and humiliated together Who seek my life to destroy it; Let those be turned back and dishonored Who delight in my hurt.
19½Ã 40:15 Let those be appalled because of their shame Who say to me, "Aha, aha!"
19½Ã 40:16 Let all who seek Thee rejoice and be glad in Thee; Let those who love Thy salvation say continually, "The LORD be magnified!"
19½Ã 40:17 Since I am afflicted and needy, Let the Lord be mindful of me; Thou art my help and my deliverer; Do not delay, O my God.
19½Ã 41:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} How blessed is he who considers the helpless; The LORD will deliver him in a day of trouble.
19½Ã 41:2 The LORD will protect him, and keep him alive, And he shall be called blessed upon the earth; And do not give him over to the desire of his enemies.
19½Ã 41:3 The LORD will sustain him upon his sickbed; In his illness, Thou dost restore him to health.
19½Ã 41:4 As for me, I said, "O LORD, be gracious to me; Heal my soul, for I have sinned against Thee."
19½Ã 41:5 My enemies speak evil against me, "When will he die, and his name perish?"
19½Ã 41:6 And when he comes to see [me], he speaks falsehood; His heart gathers wickedness to itself; When he goes outside, he tells it.
19½Ã 41:7 All who hate me whisper together against me; Against me they devise my hurt, [saying,]
19½Ã 41:8 "A wicked thing is poured out upon him, That when he lies down, he will not rise up again."
19½Ã 41:9 Even my close friend, in whom I trusted, Who ate my bread, Has lifted up his heel against me.
19½Ã 41:10 But Thou, O LORD, be gracious to me, and raise me up, That I may repay them.
19½Ã 41:11 By this I know that Thou art pleased with me, Because my enemy does not shout in triumph over me.
19½Ã 41:12 As for me, Thou dost uphold me in my integrity, And Thou dost set me in Thy presence forever.
19½Ã 41:13 Blessed be the LORD, the God of Israel, From everlasting to everlasting. Amen, and Amen.
19½Ã 42:1 {For the choir director. A Maskil of the sons of Korah.} As the deer pants for the water brooks, So my soul pants for Thee, O God.
19½Ã 42:2 My soul thirsts for God, for the living God; When shall I come and appear before God?
19½Ã 42:3 My tears have been my food day and night, While [they] say to me all day long, "Where is your God?"
19½Ã 42:4 These things I remember, and I pour out my soul within me. For I used to go along with the throng [and] lead them in procession to the house of God, With the voice of joy and thanksgiving, a multitude keeping festival.
19½Ã 42:5 Why are you in despair, O my soul? And [why] have you become disturbed within me? Hope in God, for I shall again praise Him [For] the help of His presence.
19½Ã 42:6 O my God, my soul is in despair within me; Therefore I remember Thee from the land of the Jordan, And the peaks of Hermon, from Mount Mizar.
19½Ã 42:7 Deep calls to deep at the sound of Thy waterfalls; All Thy breakers and Thy waves have rolled over me.
19½Ã 42:8 The LORD will command His lovingkindness in the daytime; And His song will be with me in the night, A prayer to the God of my life.
19½Ã 42:9 I will say to God my rock, "Why hast Thou forgotten me? Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?"
19½Ã 42:10 As a shattering of my bones, my adversaries revile me, While they say to me all day long, "Where is your God?"
19½Ã 42:11 Why are you in despair, O my soul? And why have you become disturbed within me? Hope in God, for I shall yet praise Him, The help of my countenance, and my God.
19½Ã 43:1 Vindicate me, O God, and plead my case against an ungodly nation; O deliver me from the deceitful and unjust man!
19½Ã 43:2 For Thou art the God of my strength; why hast Thou rejected me? Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?
19½Ã 43:3 O send out Thy light and Thy truth, let them lead me; Let them bring me to Thy holy hill, And to Thy dwelling places.
19½Ã 43:4 Then I will go to the altar of God, To God my exceeding joy; And upon the lyre I shall praise Thee, O God, my God.
19½Ã 43:5 Why are you in despair, O my soul? And why are you disturbed within me? Hope in God, for I shall again praise Him, The help of my countenance, and my God.
19½Ã 44:1 {For the choir director. A Maskil of the sons of Korah.} O God, we have heard with our ears, Our fathers have told us, The work that Thou didst in their days, In the days of old.
19½Ã 44:2 Thou with Thine own hand didst drive out the nations; Then Thou didst plant them; Thou didst afflict the peoples, Then Thou didst spread them abroad.
19½Ã 44:3 For by their own sword they did not possess the land; And their own arm did not save them; But Thy right hand, and Thine arm, and the light of Thy presence, For Thou didst favor them.
19½Ã 44:4 Thou art my King, O God; Command victories for Jacob.
19½Ã 44:5 Through Thee we will push back our adversaries; Through Thy name we will trample down those who rise up against us.
19½Ã 44:6 For I will not trust in my bow, Nor will my sword save me.
19½Ã 44:7 But Thou hast saved us from our adversaries, And Thou hast put to shame those who hate us.
19½Ã 44:8 In God we have boasted all day long, And we will give thanks to Thy name forever. Selah.
19½Ã 44:9 Yet Thou hast rejected [us] and brought us to dishonor, And dost not go out with our armies.
19½Ã 44:10 Thou dost cause us to turn back from the adversary; And those who hate us have taken spoil for themselves.
19½Ã 44:11 Thou dost give us as sheep to be eaten, And hast scattered us among the nations.
19½Ã 44:12 Thou dost sell Thy people cheaply, And hast not profited by their sale.
19½Ã 44:13 Thou dost make us a reproach to our neighbors, A scoffing and a derision to those around us.
19½Ã 44:14 Thou dost make us a byword among the nations, A laughingstock among the peoples.
19½Ã 44:15 All day long my dishonor is before me, And my humiliation has overwhelmed me,
19½Ã 44:16 Because of the voice of him who reproaches and reviles, Because of the presence of the enemy and the avenger.
19½Ã 44:17 All this has come upon us, but we have not forgotten Thee, And we have not dealt falsely with Thy covenant.
19½Ã 44:18 Our heart has not turned back, And our steps have not deviated from Thy way,
19½Ã 44:19 Yet Thou hast crushed us in a place of jackals, And covered us with the shadow of death.
19½Ã 44:20 If we had forgotten the name of our God, Or extended our hands to a strange god;
19½Ã 44:21 Would not God find this out? For He knows the secrets of the heart.
19½Ã 44:22 But for Thy sake we are killed all day long; We are considered as sheep to be slaughtered.
19½Ã 44:23 Arouse Thyself, why dost Thou sleep, O Lord? Awake, do not reject us forever.
19½Ã 44:24 Why dost Thou hide Thy face, And forget our affliction and our oppression?
19½Ã 44:25 For our soul has sunk down into the dust; Our body cleaves to the earth.
19½Ã 44:26 Rise up, be our help, And redeem us for the sake of Thy lovingkindness.
19½Ã 45:1 {For the choir director; according to the Shoshannim. A Maskil of the sons of} (Korah. A Song of Love.) My heart overflows with a good theme; I address my verses to the King; My tongue is the pen of a ready writer.
