19½Ã 46:1 {For the choir director. [A Psalm] of the sons of Korah, set to Alamoth. A Song.} God is our refuge and strength, A very present help in trouble.
19½Ã 46:2 Therefore we will not fear, though the earth should change, And though the mountains slip into the heart of the sea;
19½Ã 46:3 Though its waters roar [and] foam, Though the mountains quake at its swelling pride. Selah.
