19½Ã 49:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.} Hear this, all peoples; Give ear, all inhabitants of the world,
19½Ã 49:2 Both low and high, Rich and poor together.
19½Ã 49:3 My mouth will speak wisdom; And the meditation of my heart [will be] understanding.
19½Ã 49:4 I will incline my ear to a proverb; I will express my riddle on the harp.
19½Ã 49:5 Why should I fear in days of adversity, When the iniquity of my foes surrounds me,
19½Ã 49:6 Even those who trust in their wealth, And boast in the abundance of their riches?
19½Ã 49:7 No man can by any means redeem [his] brother, Or give to God a ransom for him--
19½Ã 49:8 For the redemption of his soul is costly, And he should cease [trying] forever--
19½Ã 49:9 That he should live on eternally; That he should not undergo decay.
19½Ã 49:10 For he sees [that even] wise men die; The stupid and the senseless alike perish, And leave their wealth to others.
19½Ã 49:11 Their inner thought is, [that] their houses are forever, [And] their dwelling places to all generations; They have called their lands after their own names.
