19½Ã 71:8 My mouth is filled with Thy praise, And with Thy glory all day long.
19½Ã 71:9 Do not cast me off in the time of old age; Do not forsake me when my strength fails.
19½Ã 71:10 For my enemies have spoken against me; And those who watch for my life have consulted together,
19½Ã 71:11 Saying, "God has forsaken him; Pursue and seize him, for there is no one to deliver."
19½Ã 71:12 O God, do not be far from me; O my God, hasten to my help!
19½Ã 71:13 Let those who are adversaries of my soul be ashamed [and] consumed; Let them be covered with reproach and dishonor, who seek to injure me.
19½Ã 71:14 But as for me, I will hope continually, And will praise Thee yet more and more.
19½Ã 71:15 My mouth shall tell of Thy righteousness, [And] of Thy salvation all day long; For I do not know the sum [of them.]
19½Ã 71:16 I will come with the mighty deeds of the Lord GOD; I will make mention of Thy righteousness, Thine alone.
19½Ã 71:17 O God, Thou hast taught me from my youth; And I still declare Thy wondrous deeds.
19½Ã 71:18 And even when [I am] old and gray, O God, do not forsake me, Until I declare Thy strength to [this] generation, Thy power to all who are to come.
19½Ã 71:19 For Thy righteousness, O God, [reaches] to the heavens, Thou who hast done great things; O God, who is like Thee?
19½Ã 71:20 Thou, who hast shown me many troubles and distresses, Wilt revive me again, And wilt bring me up again from the depths of the earth.
19½Ã 71:21 Mayest Thou increase my greatness, And turn [to] comfort me.
19½Ã 71:22 I will also praise Thee with a harp, [Even] Thy truth, O my God; To Thee I will sing praises with the lyre, O Thou Holy One of Israel.
19½Ã 71:23 My lips will shout for joy when I sing praises to Thee; And my soul, which Thou hast redeemed.
19½Ã 71:24 My tongue also will utter Thy righteousness all day long; For they are ashamed, for they are humiliated who seek my hurt.
19½Ã 72:1 {[A Psalm] of Solomon.} Give the king Thy judgments, O God, And Thy righteousness to the king's son.
19½Ã 72:2 May he judge Thy people with righteousness, And Thine afflicted with justice.
19½Ã 72:3 Let the mountains bring peace to the people, And the hills in righteousness.
19½Ã 72:4 May he vindicate the afflicted of the people, Save the children of the needy, And crush the oppressor.
19½Ã 72:5 Let them fear Thee while the sun [endures], And as long as the moon, throughout all generations.
19½Ã 72:6 May he come down like rain upon the mown grass, Like showers that water the earth.
19½Ã 72:7 In his days may the righteous flourish, And abundance of peace till the moon is no more.
19½Ã 72:8 May he also rule from sea to sea, And from the River to the ends of the earth.
19½Ã 72:9 Let the nomads of the desert bow before him; And his enemies lick the dust.
19½Ã 72:10 Let the kings of Tarshish and of the islands bring presents; The kings of Sheba and Seba offer gifts.
19½Ã 72:11 And let all kings bow down before him, All nations serve him.
19½Ã 72:12 For he will deliver the needy when he cries for help, The afflicted also, and him who has no helper.
19½Ã 72:13 He will have compassion on the poor and needy, And the lives of the needy he will save.
19½Ã 72:14 He will rescue their life from oppression and violence; And their blood will be precious in his sight;
19½Ã 72:15 So may he live; and may the gold of Sheba be given to him; And let them pray for him continually; Let them bless him all day long.
19½Ã 72:16 May there be abundance of grain in the earth on top of the mountains; Its fruit will wave like [the cedars of] Lebanon; And may those from the city flourish like vegetation of the earth.
19½Ã 72:17 May his name endure forever; May his name increase as long as the sun [shines]; And let [men] bless themselves by him; Let all nations call him blessed.
19½Ã 72:18 Blessed be the LORD God, the God of Israel, Who alone works wonders.
19½Ã 72:19 And blessed be His glorious name forever; And may the whole earth be filled with His glory. Amen, and Amen.
19½Ã 72:20 The prayers of David the son of Jesse are ended.
19½Ã 73:1 {A Psalm of Asaph.} Surely God is good to Israel, To those who are pure in heart!
19½Ã 73:2 But as for me, my feet came close to stumbling; My steps had almost slipped.
19½Ã 73:3 For I was envious of the arrogant, [As] I saw the prosperity of the wicked.
19½Ã 73:4 For there are no pains in their death; And their body is fat.
19½Ã 73:5 They are not in trouble [as other] men; Nor are they plagued like mankind.
19½Ã 73:6 Therefore pride is their necklace; The garment of violence covers them.
19½Ã 73:7 Their eye bulges from fatness; The imaginations of [their] heart run riot.
19½Ã 73:8 They mock, and wickedly speak of oppression; They speak from on high.
19½Ã 73:9 They have set their mouth against the heavens, And their tongue parades through the earth.
19½Ã 73:10 Therefore his people return to this place; And waters of abundance are drunk by them.
19½Ã 73:11 And they say, "How does God know? And is there knowledge with the Most High?"
19½Ã 73:12 Behold, these are the wicked; And always at ease, they have increased [in] wealth.
19½Ã 73:13 Surely in vain I have kept my heart pure, And washed my hands in innocence;
19½Ã 73:14 For I have been stricken all day long, And chastened every morning.
19½Ã 73:15 If I had said, "I will speak thus," Behold, I should have betrayed the generation of Thy children.
19½Ã 73:16 When I pondered to understand this, It was troublesome in my sight
19½Ã 73:17 Until I came into the sanctuary of God; [Then] I perceived their end.
19½Ã 73:18 Surely Thou dost set them in slippery places; Thou dost cast them down to destruction.
19½Ã 73:19 How they are destroyed in a moment! They are utterly swept away by sudden terrors!
19½Ã 73:20 Like a dream when one awakes, O Lord, when aroused, Thou wilt despise their form.
19½Ã 73:21 When my heart was embittered, And I was pierced within,
19½Ã 73:22 Then I was senseless and ignorant; I was [like] a beast before Thee.
19½Ã 73:23 Nevertheless I am continually with Thee; Thou hast taken hold of my right hand.
19½Ã 73:24 With Thy counsel Thou wilt guide me, And afterward receive me to glory.
19½Ã 73:25 Whom have I in heaven [but Thee]? And besides Thee, I desire nothing on earth.
19½Ã 73:26 My flesh and my heart may fail, But God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever.
19½Ã 73:27 For, behold, those who are far from Thee will perish; Thou hast destroyed all those who are unfaithful to Thee.
19½Ã 73:28 But as for me, the nearness of God is my good; I have made the Lord GOD my refuge, That I may tell of all Thy works.
19½Ã 74:1 {A Maskil of Asaph.} O God, why hast Thou rejected [us] forever? Why does Thine anger smoke against the sheep of Thy pasture?
19½Ã 74:2 Remember Thy congregation, which Thou hast purchased of old, Which Thou hast redeemed to be the tribe of Thine inheritance; [And] this Mount Zion, where Thou hast dwelt.
19½Ã 74:3 Turn Thy footsteps toward the perpetual ruins; The enemy has damaged everything within the sanctuary.
19½Ã 74:4 Thine adversaries have roared in the midst of Thy meeting place; They have set up their own standards for signs.
19½Ã 74:5 It seems as if one had lifted up [His] axe in a forest of trees.
19½Ã 74:6 And now all its carved work They smash with hatchet and hammers.
19½Ã 74:7 They have burned Thy sanctuary to the ground; They have defiled the dwelling place of Thy name.
19½Ã 74:8 They said in their heart, "Let us completely subdue them." They have burned all the meeting places of God in the land.
19½Ã 74:9 We do not see our signs; There is no longer any prophet, Nor is there any among us who knows how long.
19½Ã 74:10 How long, O God, will the adversary revile, [And] the enemy spurn Thy name forever?
19½Ã 74:11 Why dost Thou withdraw Thy hand, even Thy right hand? From within Thy bosom, destroy [them]!
19½Ã 74:12 Yet God is my king from of old, Who works deeds of deliverance in the midst of the earth.
19½Ã 74:13 Thou didst divide the sea by Thy strength; Thou didst break the heads of the sea monsters in the waters.
19½Ã 74:14 Thou didst crush the heads of Leviathan; Thou didst give him as food for the creatures of the wilderness.
19½Ã 74:15 Thou didst break open springs and torrents; Thou didst dry up ever-flowing streams.
19½Ã 74:16 Thine is the day, Thine also is the night; Thou hast prepared the light and the sun.
19½Ã 74:17 Thou hast established all the boundaries of the earth; Thou hast made summer and winter.
19½Ã 74:18 Remember this, O LORD, that the enemy has reviled; And a foolish people has spurned Thy name.
19½Ã 74:19 Do not deliver the soul of Thy turtledove to the wild beast; Do not forget the life of Thine afflicted forever.
19½Ã 74:20 Consider the covenant; For the dark places of the land are full of the habitations of violence.
19½Ã 74:21 Let not the oppressed return dishonored; Let the afflicted and needy praise Thy name.
19½Ã 74:22 Do arise, O God, [and] plead Thine own cause; Remember how the foolish man reproaches Thee all day long.
19½Ã 74:23 Do not forget the voice of Thine adversaries, The uproar of those who rise against Thee which ascends continually.
19½Ã 75:1 {For the choir director; [set to] Al-tashheth. A Psalm of Asaph, a Song.} We give thanks to Thee, O God, we give thanks, For Thy name is near; Men declare Thy wondrous works.
19½Ã 75:2 "When I select an appointed time, It is I who judge with equity.
19½Ã 75:3 "The earth and all who dwell in it melt; It is I who have firmly set its pillars. Selah.
19½Ã 75:4 "I said to the boastful, 'Do not boast,' And to the wicked, 'Do not lift up the horn;
19½Ã 75:5 Do not lift up your horn on high, Do not speak with insolent pride. ' "
19½Ã 75:6 For not from the east, nor from the west, Nor from the desert [comes] exaltation;
19½Ã 75:7 But God is the Judge; He puts down one, and exalts another.
19½Ã 75:8 For a cup is in the hand of the LORD, and the wine foams; It is well mixed, and He pours out of this; Surely all the wicked of the earth must drain [and] drink down its dregs.
19½Ã 75:9 But as for me, I will declare [it] forever; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.
