19½Ã 76:5 The stouthearted were plundered; They sank into sleep; And none of the warriors could use his hands.
19½Ã 76:6 At Thy rebuke, O God of Jacob, Both rider and horse were cast into a dead sleep.
19½Ã 76:7 Thou, even Thou, art to be feared; And who may stand in Thy presence when once Thou art angry?
19½Ã 76:8 Thou didst cause judgment to be heard from heaven; The earth feared, and was still,
