19½Ã 77:1 {For the choir director; according to Jeduthun. A Psalm of Asaph.} My voice [rises] to God, and I will cry aloud; My voice [rises] to God, and He will hear me.
19½Ã 77:2 In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord; In the night my hand was stretched out without weariness; My soul refused to be comforted.
19½Ã 77:3 [When] I remember God, then I am disturbed; [When] I sigh, then my spirit grows faint. Selah.
19½Ã 77:4 Thou hast held my eyelids [open]; I am so troubled that I cannot speak.
19½Ã 77:5 I have considered the days of old, The years of long ago.
19½Ã 77:6 I will remember my song in the night; I will meditate with my heart; And my spirit ponders.
19½Ã 77:7 Will the Lord reject forever? And will He never be favorable again?
19½Ã 77:8 Has His lovingkindness ceased forever? Has [His] promise come to an end forever?
19½Ã 77:9 Has God forgotten to be gracious? Or has He in anger withdrawn His compassion? Selah.
19½Ã 77:10 Then I said, "It is my grief, That the right hand of the Most High has changed."
19½Ã 77:11 I shall remember the deeds of the LORD; Surely I will remember Thy wonders of old.
19½Ã 77:12 I will meditate on all Thy work, And muse on Thy deeds.
19½Ã 77:13 Thy way, O God, is holy; What god is great like our God?
19½Ã 77:14 Thou art the God who workest wonders; Thou hast made known Thy strength among the peoples.
19½Ã 77:15 Thou hast by Thy power redeemed Thy people, The sons of Jacob and Joseph. Selah.
19½Ã 77:16 The waters saw Thee, O God; The waters saw Thee, they were in anguish; The deeps also trembled.
19½Ã 77:17 The clouds poured out water; The skies gave forth a sound; Thy arrows flashed here and there.
19½Ã 77:18 The sound of Thy thunder was in the whirlwind; The lightnings lit up the world; The earth trembled and shook.
19½Ã 77:19 Thy way was in the sea, And Thy paths in the mighty waters, And Thy footprints may not be known.
19½Ã 77:20 Thou didst lead Thy people like a flock, By the hand of Moses and Aaron.
19½Ã 78:1 {A Maskil of Asaph.} Listen, O my people, to my instruction; Incline your ears to the words of my mouth.
19½Ã 78:2 I will open my mouth in a parable; I will utter dark sayings of old,
19½Ã 78:3 Which we have heard and known, And our fathers have told us.
19½Ã 78:4 We will not conceal them from their children, But tell to the generation to come the praises of the LORD, And His strength and His wondrous works that He has done.
19½Ã 78:5 For He established a testimony in Jacob, And appointed a law in Israel, Which He commanded our fathers, That they should teach them to their children,
19½Ã 78:6 That the generation to come might know, [even] the children [yet] to be born, [That] they may arise and tell [them] to their children,
19½Ã 78:7 That they should put their confidence in God, And not forget the works of God, But keep His commandments,
19½Ã 78:8 And not be like their fathers, A stubborn and rebellious generation, A generation that did not prepare its heart, And whose spirit was not faithful to God.
19½Ã 78:9 The sons of Ephraim were archers equipped with bows, [Yet] they turned back in the day of battle.
19½Ã 78:10 They did not keep the covenant of God, And refused to walk in His law;
19½Ã 78:11 And they forgot His deeds, And His miracles that He had shown them.
19½Ã 78:12 He wrought wonders before their fathers, In the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.
19½Ã 78:13 He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; And He made the waters stand up like a heap.
19½Ã 78:14 Then He led them with the cloud by day, And all the night with a light of fire.
19½Ã 78:15 He split the rocks in the wilderness, And gave [them] abundant drink like the ocean depths.
19½Ã 78:16 He brought forth streams also from the rock, And caused waters to run down like rivers.
19½Ã 78:17 Yet they still continued to sin against Him, To rebel against the Most High in the desert.
19½Ã 78:18 And in their heart they put God to the test By asking food according to their desire.
19½Ã 78:19 Then they spoke against God; They said, "Can God prepare a table in the wilderness?
19½Ã 78:20 "Behold, He struck the rock, so that waters gushed out, And streams were overflowing; Can He give bread also? Will He provide meat for His people?"
19½Ã 78:21 Therefore the LORD heard and was full of wrath, And a fire was kindled against Jacob, And anger also mounted against Israel;
19½Ã 78:22 Because they did not believe in God, And did not trust in His salvation.
19½Ã 78:23 Yet He commanded the clouds above, And opened the doors of heaven;
19½Ã 78:24 And He rained down manna upon them to eat, And gave them food from heaven.
19½Ã 78:25 Man did eat the bread of angels; He sent them food in abundance.
19½Ã 78:26 He caused the east wind to blow in the heavens; And by His power He directed the south wind.
19½Ã 78:27 When He rained meat upon them like the dust, Even winged fowl like the sand of the seas,
19½Ã 78:28 Then He let [them] fall in the midst of their camp, Round about their dwellings.
19½Ã 78:29 So they ate and were well filled; And their desire He gave to them.
19½Ã 78:30 Before they had satisfied their desire, While their food was in their mouths,
19½Ã 78:31 The anger of God rose against them, And killed some of their stoutest ones, And subdued the choice men of Israel.
19½Ã 78:32 In spite of all this they still sinned, And did not believe in His wonderful works.
19½Ã 78:33 So He brought their days to an end in futility, And their years in sudden terror.
19½Ã 78:34 When He killed them, then they sought Him, And returned and searched diligently for God;
19½Ã 78:35 And they remembered that God was their rock, And the Most High God their Redeemer.
19½Ã 78:36 But they deceived Him with their mouth, And lied to Him with their tongue.
19½Ã 78:37 For their heart was not steadfast toward Him, Nor were they faithful in His covenant.
19½Ã 78:38 But He, being compassionate, forgave [their] iniquity, and did not destroy [them]; And often He restrained His anger, And did not arouse all His wrath.
19½Ã 78:39 Thus He remembered that they were but flesh, A wind that passes and does not return.
19½Ã 78:40 How often they rebelled against Him in the wilderness, And grieved Him in the desert!
19½Ã 78:41 And again and again they tempted God, And pained the Holy One of Israel.
19½Ã 78:42 They did not remember His power, The day when He redeemed them from the adversary,
19½Ã 78:43 When He performed His signs in Egypt, And His marvels in the field of Zoan,
19½Ã 78:44 And turned their rivers to blood, And their streams, they could not drink.
19½Ã 78:45 He sent among them swarms of flies, which devoured them, And frogs which destroyed them.
19½Ã 78:46 He gave also their crops to the grasshopper, And the product of their labor to the locust.
19½Ã 78:47 He destroyed their vines with hailstones, And their sycamore trees with frost.
19½Ã 78:48 He gave over their cattle also to the hailstones, And their herds to bolts of lightning.
19½Ã 78:49 He sent upon them His burning anger, Fury, and indignation, and trouble, A band of destroying angels.
19½Ã 78:50 He leveled a path for His anger; He did not spare their soul from death, But gave over their life to the plague,
