19½Ã 85:5 Wilt Thou be angry with us forever? Wilt Thou prolong Thine anger to all generations?
19½Ã 85:6 Wilt Thou not Thyself revive us again, That Thy people may rejoice in Thee?
19½Ã 85:7 Show us Thy lovingkindness, O LORD, And grant us Thy salvation.
19½Ã 85:8 I will hear what God the LORD will say; For He will speak peace to His people, to His godly ones; But let them not turn back to folly.
19½Ã 85:9 Surely His salvation is near to those who fear Him, That glory may dwell in our land.
19½Ã 85:10 Lovingkindness and truth have met together; Righteousness and peace have kissed each other.
19½Ã 85:11 Truth springs from the earth; And righteousness looks down from heaven.
