19½Ã 86:9 All nations whom Thou hast made shall come and worship before Thee, O Lord; And they shall glorify Thy name.
19½Ã 86:10 For Thou art great and doest wondrous deeds; Thou alone art God.
19½Ã 86:11 Teach me Thy way, O LORD; I will walk in Thy truth; Unite my heart to fear Thy name.
19½Ã 86:12 I will give thanks to Thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart, And will glorify Thy name forever.
19½Ã 86:13 For Thy lovingkindness toward me is great, And Thou hast delivered my soul from the depths of Sheol.
19½Ã 86:14 O God, arrogant men have risen up against me, And a band of violent men have sought my life, And they have not set Thee before them.
19½Ã 86:15 But Thou, O Lord, art a God merciful and gracious, Slow to anger and abundant in lovingkindness and truth.
19½Ã 86:16 Turn to me, and be gracious to me; Oh grant Thy strength to Thy servant, And save the son of Thy handmaid.
19½Ã 86:17 Show me a sign for good, That those who hate me may see [it], and be ashamed, Because Thou, O LORD, hast helped me and comforted me.
19½Ã 87:1 {A Psalm of the sons of Korah. A Song.} His foundation is in the holy mountains.
