19½Ã 96:8 Ascribe to the LORD the glory of His name; Bring an offering, and come into His courts.
19½Ã 96:9 Worship the LORD in holy attire; Tremble before Him, all the earth.
19½Ã 96:10 Say among the nations, "The LORD reigns; Indeed, the world is firmly established, it will not be moved; He will judge the peoples with equity."
19½Ã 96:11 Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice; Let the sea roar, and all it contains;
19½Ã 96:12 Let the field exult, and all that is in it. Then all the trees of the forest will sing for joy
19½Ã 96:13 Before the LORD, for He is coming; For He is coming to judge the earth. He will judge the world in righteousness, And the peoples in His faithfulness.
19½Ã 97:1 The LORD reigns; let the earth rejoice; Let the many islands be glad.
19½Ã 97:2 Clouds and thick darkness surround Him; Righteousness and justice are the foundation of His throne.
19½Ã 97:3 Fire goes before Him, And burns up His adversaries round about.
19½Ã 97:4 His lightnings lit up the world; The earth saw and trembled.
19½Ã 97:5 The mountains melted like wax at the presence of the LORD, At the presence of the Lord of the whole earth.
19½Ã 97:6 The heavens declare His righteousness, And all the peoples have seen His glory.
19½Ã 97:7 Let all those be ashamed who serve graven images, Who boast themselves of idols; Worship Him, all you gods.
19½Ã 97:8 Zion heard [this] and was glad, And the daughters of Judah have rejoiced Because of Thy judgments, O LORD.
19½Ã 97:9 For Thou art the LORD Most High over all the earth; Thou art exalted far above all gods.
19½Ã 97:10 Hate evil, you who love the LORD, Who preserves the souls of His godly ones; He delivers them from the hand of the wicked.
19½Ã 97:11 Light is sown [like seed] for the righteous, And gladness for the upright in heart.
19½Ã 97:12 Be glad in the LORD, you righteous ones; And give thanks to His holy name.
19½Ã 98:1 {A Psalm.} O Sing to the LORD a new song, For He has done wonderful things, His right hand and His holy arm have gained the victory for Him.
19½Ã 98:2 The LORD has made known His salvation; He has revealed His righteousness in the sight of the nations.
19½Ã 98:3 He has remembered His lovingkindness and His faithfulness to the house of Israel; All the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.
19½Ã 98:4 Shout joyfully to the LORD, all the earth; Break forth and sing for joy and sing praises.
19½Ã 98:5 Sing praises to the LORD with the lyre; With the lyre and the sound of melody.
19½Ã 98:6 With trumpets and the sound of the horn Shout joyfully before the King, the LORD.
19½Ã 98:7 Let the sea roar and all it contains, The world and those who dwell in it.
19½Ã 98:8 Let the rivers clap their hands; Let the mountains sing together for joy
19½Ã 98:9 Before the LORD; for He is coming to judge the earth; He will judge the world with righteousness, And the peoples with equity.
19½Ã 99:1 The LORD reigns, let the peoples tremble; He is enthroned [above] the cherubim, let the earth shake!
19½Ã 99:2 The LORD is great in Zion, And He is exalted above all the peoples.
19½Ã 99:3 Let them praise Thy great and awesome name; Holy is He.
19½Ã 99:4 And the strength of the King loves justice; Thou hast established equity; Thou hast executed justice and righteousness in Jacob.
19½Ã 99:5 Exalt the LORD our God, And worship at His footstool; Holy is He.
19½Ã 99:6 Moses and Aaron were among His priests, And Samuel was among those who called on His name; They called upon the LORD, and He answered them.
19½Ã 99:7 He spoke to them in the pillar of cloud; They kept His testimonies, And the statute that He gave them.
19½Ã 99:8 O LORD our God, Thou didst answer them; Thou wast a forgiving God to them, And [yet] an avenger of their [evil] deeds.
19½Ã 99:9 Exalt the LORD our God, And worship at His holy hill; For holy is the LORD our God.
19½Ã 100:1 {A Psalm for Thanksgiving.} Shout joyfully to the LORD, all the earth.
19½Ã 100:2 Serve the LORD with gladness; Come before Him with joyful singing.
19½Ã 100:3 Know that the LORD Himself is God; It is He who has made us, and not we ourselves; [We are] His people and the sheep of His pasture.
19½Ã 100:4 Enter His gates with thanksgiving, [And] His courts with praise. Give thanks to Him; bless His name.
19½Ã 100:5 For the LORD is good; His lovingkindness is everlasting, And His faithfulness to all generations.
19½Ã 101:1 {A Psalm of David.} I will sing of lovingkindness and justice, To Thee, O LORD, I will sing praises.
19½Ã 101:2 I will give heed to the blameless way. When wilt Thou come to me? I will walk within my house in the integrity of my heart.
19½Ã 101:3 I will set no worthless thing before my eyes; I hate the work of those who fall away; It shall not fasten its grip on me.
19½Ã 101:4 A perverse heart shall depart from me; I will know no evil.
19½Ã 101:5 Whoever secretly slanders his neighbor, him I will destroy; No one who has a haughty look and an arrogant heart will I endure.
19½Ã 101:6 My eyes shall be upon the faithful of the land, that they may dwell with me; He who walks in a blameless way is the one who will minister to me.
19½Ã 101:7 He who practices deceit shall not dwell within my house; He who speaks falsehood shall not maintain his position before me.
19½Ã 101:8 Every morning I will destroy all the wicked of the land, So as to cut off from the city of the LORD all those who do iniquity.
19½Ã 102:1 {A Prayer of the Afflicted, when he is faint, and pours out his complaint} (before the LORD.) Hear my prayer, O LORD! And let my cry for help come to Thee.
19½Ã 102:2 Do not hide Thy face from me in the day of my distress; Incline Thine ear to me; In the day when I call answer me quickly.
19½Ã 102:3 For my days have been consumed in smoke, And my bones have been scorched like a hearth.
19½Ã 102:4 My heart has been smitten like grass and has withered away, Indeed, I forget to eat my bread.
19½Ã 102:5 Because of the loudness of my groaning My bones cling to my flesh.
19½Ã 102:6 I resemble a pelican of the wilderness; I have become like an owl of the waste places.
19½Ã 102:7 I lie awake, I have become like a lonely bird on a housetop.
19½Ã 102:8 My enemies have reproached me all day long; Those who deride me have used my [name] as a curse.
19½Ã 102:9 For I have eaten ashes like bread, And mingled my drink with weeping,
19½Ã 102:10 Because of Thine indignation and Thy wrath; For Thou hast lifted me up and cast me away.
19½Ã 102:11 My days are like a lengthened shadow; And I wither away like grass.
19½Ã 102:12 But Thou, O LORD, dost abide forever; And Thy name to all generations.
19½Ã 102:13 Thou wilt arise [and] have compassion on Zion; For it is time to be gracious to her, For the appointed time has come.
19½Ã 102:14 Surely Thy servants find pleasure in her stones, And feel pity for her dust.
19½Ã 102:15 So the nations will fear the name of the LORD, And all the kings of the earth Thy glory.
19½Ã 102:16 For the LORD has built up Zion; He has appeared in His glory.
19½Ã 102:17 He has regarded the prayer of the destitute, And has not despised their prayer.
19½Ã 102:18 This will be written for the generation to come; That a people yet to be created may praise the LORD.
19½Ã 102:19 For He looked down from His holy height; From heaven the LORD gazed upon the earth,
19½Ã 102:20 To hear the groaning of the prisoner; To set free those who were doomed to death;
19½Ã 102:21 That [men] may tell of the name of the LORD in Zion, And His praise in Jerusalem;
19½Ã 102:22 When the peoples are gathered together, And the kingdoms, to serve the LORD.
19½Ã 102:23 He has weakened my strength in the way; He has shortened my days.
19½Ã 102:24 I say, "O my God, do not take me away in the midst of my days, Thy years are throughout all generations.
19½Ã 102:25 "Of old Thou didst found the earth; And the heavens are the work of Thy hands.
19½Ã 102:26 "Even they will perish, but Thou dost endure; And all of them will wear out like a garment; Like clothing Thou wilt change them, and they will be changed.
19½Ã 102:27 "But Thou art the same, And Thy years will not come to an end.
19½Ã 102:28 "The children of Thy servants will continue, And their descendants will be established before Thee."
19½Ã 103:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} Bless the LORD, O my soul; And all that is within me, [bless] His holy name.
19½Ã 103:2 Bless the LORD, O my soul, And forget none of His benefits;
19½Ã 103:3 Who pardons all your iniquities; Who heals all your diseases;
19½Ã 103:4 Who redeems your life from the pit; Who crowns you with lovingkindness and compassion;
19½Ã 103:5 Who satisfies your years with good things, [So that] your youth is renewed like the eagle.
19½Ã 103:6 The LORD performs righteous deeds, And judgments for all who are oppressed.
19½Ã 103:7 He made known His ways to Moses, His acts to the sons of Israel.
19½Ã 103:8 The LORD is compassionate and gracious, Slow to anger and abounding in lovingkindness.
19½Ã 103:9 He will not always strive [with us]; Nor will He keep [His anger] forever.
19½Ã 103:10 He has not dealt with us according to our sins, Nor rewarded us according to our iniquities.
19½Ã 103:11 For as high as the heavens are above the earth, So great is His lovingkindness toward those who fear Him.
19½Ã 103:12 As far as the east is from the west, So far has He removed our transgressions from us.
19½Ã 103:13 Just as a father has compassion on [his] children, So the LORD has compassion on those who fear Him.
19½Ã 103:14 For He Himself knows our frame; He is mindful that we are [but] dust.
19½Ã 103:15 As for man, his days are like grass; As a flower of the field, so he flourishes.
19½Ã 103:16 When the wind has passed over it, it is no more; And its place acknowledges it no longer.
19½Ã 103:17 But the lovingkindness of the LORD is from everlasting to everlasting on those who fear Him, And His righteousness to children's children,
19½Ã 103:18 To those who keep His covenant, And who remember His precepts to do them.
19½Ã 103:19 The LORD has established His throne in the heavens; And His sovereignty rules over all.
19½Ã 103:20 Bless the LORD, you His angels, Mighty in strength, who perform His word, Obeying the voice of His word!
19½Ã 103:21 Bless the LORD, all you His hosts, You who serve Him, doing His will.
19½Ã 103:22 Bless the LORD, all you works of His, In all places of His dominion; Bless the LORD, O my soul!
19½Ã 104:1 Bless the LORD, O my soul! O LORD my God, Thou art very great; Thou art clothed with splendor and majesty,
19½Ã 104:2 Covering Thyself with light as with a cloak, Stretching out heaven like a [tent] curtain.
19½Ã 104:3 He lays the beams of His upper chambers in the waters; He makes the clouds His chariot; He walks upon the wings of the wind;
19½Ã 104:4 He makes the winds His messengers, Flaming fire His ministers.
19½Ã 104:5 He established the earth upon its foundations, So that it will not totter forever and ever.
19½Ã 104:6 Thou didst cover it with the deep as with a garment; The waters were standing above the mountains.
19½Ã 104:7 At Thy rebuke they fled; At the sound of Thy thunder they hurried away.
19½Ã 104:8 The mountains rose; the valleys sank down To the place which Thou didst establish for them.
19½Ã 104:9 Thou didst set a boundary that they may not pass over; That they may not return to cover the earth.
19½Ã 104:10 He sends forth springs in the valleys; They flow between the mountains;
19½Ã 104:11 They give drink to every beast of the field; The wild donkeys quench their thirst.
19½Ã 104:12 Beside them the birds of the heavens dwell; They lift up [their] voices among the branches.
19½Ã 104:13 He waters the mountains from His upper chambers; The earth is satisfied with the fruit of His works.
19½Ã 104:14 He causes the grass to grow for the cattle, And vegetation for the labor of man, So that he may bring forth food from the earth,
19½Ã 104:15 And wine which makes man's heart glad, So that he may make [his] face glisten with oil, And food which sustains man's heart.
19½Ã 104:16 The trees of the LORD drink their fill, The cedars of Lebanon which He planted,
19½Ã 104:17 Where the birds build their nests, [And] the stork, whose home is the fir trees.
19½Ã 104:18 The high mountains are for the wild goats; The cliffs are a refuge for the rock badgers.
19½Ã 104:19 He made the moon for the seasons; The sun knows the place of its setting.
19½Ã 104:20 Thou dost appoint darkness and it becomes night, In which all the beasts of the forest prowl about.
19½Ã 104:21 The young lions roar after their prey, And seek their food from God.
19½Ã 104:22 [When] the sun rises they withdraw, And lie down in their dens.
19½Ã 104:23 Man goes forth to his work And to his labor until evening.
19½Ã 104:24 O LORD, how many are Thy works! In wisdom Thou hast made them all; The earth is full of Thy possessions.
19½Ã 104:25 There is the sea, great and broad, In which are swarms without number, Animals both small and great.
19½Ã 104:26 There the ships move along, [And] Leviathan, which Thou hast formed to sport in it.
19½Ã 104:27 They all wait for Thee, To give them their food in due season.
19½Ã 104:28 Thou dost give to them, they gather [it] up; Thou dost open Thy hand, they are satisfied with good.
19½Ã 104:29 Thou dost hide Thy face, they are dismayed; Thou dost take away their spirit, they expire, And return to their dust.
19½Ã 104:30 Thou dost send forth Thy Spirit, they are created; And Thou dost renew the face of the ground.
19½Ã 104:31 Let the glory of the LORD endure forever; Let the LORD be glad in His works;
19½Ã 104:32 He looks at the earth, and it trembles; He touches the mountains, and they smoke.
19½Ã 104:33 I will sing to the LORD as long as I live; I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.
19½Ã 104:34 Let my meditation be pleasing to Him; As for me, I shall be glad in the LORD.
19½Ã 104:35 Let sinners be consumed from the earth, And let the wicked be no more. Bless the LORD, O my soul. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 105:1 Oh give thanks to the LORD, call upon His name; Make known His deeds among the peoples.
19½Ã 105:2 Sing to Him, sing praises to Him; Speak of all His wonders.
19½Ã 105:3 Glory in His holy name; Let the heart of those who seek the LORD be glad.
19½Ã 105:4 Seek the LORD and His strength; Seek His face continually.
19½Ã 105:5 Remember His wonders which He has done, His marvels, and the judgments uttered by His mouth,
19½Ã 105:6 O seed of Abraham, His servant, O sons of Jacob, His chosen ones!
19½Ã 105:7 He is the LORD our God; His judgments are in all the earth.
19½Ã 105:8 He has remembered His covenant forever, The word which He commanded to a thousand generations,
19½Ã 105:9 [The covenant] which He made with Abraham, And His oath to Isaac.
19½Ã 105:10 Then He confirmed it to Jacob for a statute, To Israel as an everlasting covenant,
19½Ã 105:11 Saying, "To you I will give the land of Canaan As the portion of your inheritance,"
19½Ã 105:12 When they were only a few men in number, Very few, and strangers in it.
19½Ã 105:13 And they wandered about from nation to nation, From [one] kingdom to another people.
19½Ã 105:14 He permitted no man to oppress them, And He reproved kings for their sakes£º
19½Ã 105:15 "Do not touch My anointed ones, And do My prophets no harm."
19½Ã 105:16 And He called for a famine upon the land; He broke the whole staff of bread.
19½Ã 105:17 He sent a man before them, Joseph, [who] was sold as a slave.
19½Ã 105:18 They afflicted his feet with fetters, He himself was laid in irons;
19½Ã 105:19 Until the time that his word came to pass, The word of the LORD tested him.
19½Ã 105:20 The king sent and released him, The ruler of peoples, and set him free.
19½Ã 105:21 He made him lord of his house, And ruler over all his possessions,
19½Ã 105:22 To imprison his princes at will, That he might teach his elders wisdom.
19½Ã 105:23 Israel also came into Egypt; Thus Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.
19½Ã 105:24 And He caused His people to be very fruitful, And made them stronger than their adversaries.
19½Ã 105:25 He turned their heart to hate His people, To deal craftily with His servants.
19½Ã 105:26 He sent Moses His servant, [And] Aaron whom He had chosen.
19½Ã 105:27 They performed His wondrous acts among them, And miracles in the land of Ham.
19½Ã 105:28 He sent darkness and made [it] dark; And they did not rebel against His words.
19½Ã 105:29 He turned their waters into blood, And caused their fish to die.
19½Ã 105:30 Their land swarmed with frogs [Even] in the chambers of their kings.
19½Ã 105:31 He spoke, and there came a swarm of flies [And] gnats in all their territory.
19½Ã 105:32 He gave them hail for rain, [And] flaming fire in their land.
19½Ã 105:33 He struck down their vines also and their fig trees, And shattered the trees of their territory.
19½Ã 105:34 He spoke, and locusts came, And young locusts, even without number,
19½Ã 105:35 And ate up all vegetation in their land, And ate up the fruit of their ground.
19½Ã 105:36 He also struck down all the first-born in their land, The first fruits of all their vigor.
19½Ã 105:37 Then He brought them out with silver and gold; And among His tribes there was not one who stumbled.
19½Ã 105:38 Egypt was glad when they departed; For the dread of them had fallen upon them.
19½Ã 105:39 He spread a cloud for a covering, And fire to illumine by night.
19½Ã 105:40 They asked, and He brought quail, And satisfied them with the bread of heaven.
19½Ã 105:41 He opened the rock, and water flowed out; It ran in the dry places [like] a river.
19½Ã 105:42 For He remembered His holy word [With] Abraham His servant;
19½Ã 105:43 And He brought forth His people with joy, His chosen ones with a joyful shout.
19½Ã 105:44 He gave them also the lands of the nations, That they might take possession of [the fruit of] the peoples' labor,
19½Ã 105:45 So that they might keep His statutes, And observe His laws, Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 106:1 Praise the LORD! Oh give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 106:2 Who can speak of the mighty deeds of the LORD, Or can show forth all His praise?
19½Ã 106:3 How blessed are those who keep justice, Who practice righteousness at all times!
19½Ã 106:4 Remember me, O LORD, in [Thy] favor toward Thy people; Visit me with Thy salvation,
19½Ã 106:5 That I may see the prosperity of Thy chosen ones, That I may rejoice in the gladness of Thy nation, That I may glory with Thine inheritance.
19½Ã 106:6 We have sinned like our fathers, We have committed iniquity, we have behaved wickedly.
19½Ã 106:7 Our fathers in Egypt did not understand Thy wonders; They did not remember Thine abundant kindnesses, But rebelled by the sea, at the Red Sea.
19½Ã 106:8 Nevertheless He saved them for the sake of His name, That He might make His power known.
19½Ã 106:9 Thus He rebuked the Red Sea and it dried up; And He led them through the deeps, as through the wilderness.
19½Ã 106:10 So He saved them from the hand of the one who hated [them,] And redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.
19½Ã 106:11 And the waters covered their adversaries; Not one of them was left.
19½Ã 106:12 Then they believed His words; They sang His praise.
19½Ã 106:13 They quickly forgot His works; They did not wait for His counsel,
19½Ã 106:14 But craved intensely in the wilderness, And tempted God in the desert.
19½Ã 106:15 So He gave them their request, But sent a wasting disease among them.
19½Ã 106:16 When they became envious of Moses in the camp, And of Aaron, the holy one of the LORD,
19½Ã 106:17 The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, And engulfed the company of Abiram.
19½Ã 106:18 And a fire blazed up in their company; The flame consumed the wicked.
19½Ã 106:19 They made a calf in Horeb, And worshiped a molten image.
19½Ã 106:20 Thus they exchanged their glory For the image of an ox that eats grass.
19½Ã 106:21 They forgot God their Savior, Who had done great things in Egypt,
19½Ã 106:22 Wonders in the land of Ham, [And] awesome things by the Red Sea.
19½Ã 106:23 Therefore He said that He would destroy them, Had not Moses His chosen one stood in the breach before Him, To turn away His wrath from destroying [them.]
19½Ã 106:24 Then they despised the pleasant land; They did not believe in His word,
19½Ã 106:25 But grumbled in their tents; They did not listen to the voice of the LORD.
19½Ã 106:26 Therefore He swore to them, That He would cast them down in the wilderness,
19½Ã 106:27 And that He would cast their seed among the nations, And scatter them in the lands.
19½Ã 106:28 They joined themselves also to Baal-peor, And ate sacrifices offered to the dead.
19½Ã 106:29 Thus they provoked [Him] to anger with their deeds; And the plague broke out among them.
19½Ã 106:30 Then Phinehas stood up and interposed; And so the plague was stayed.
19½Ã 106:31 And it was reckoned to him for righteousness, To all generations forever.
19½Ã 106:32 They also provoked [Him] to wrath at the waters of Meribah, So that it went hard with Moses on their account;
19½Ã 106:33 Because they were rebellious against His Spirit, He spoke rashly with his lips.
19½Ã 106:34 They did not destroy the peoples, As the LORD commanded them,
19½Ã 106:35 But they mingled with the nations, And learned their practices,
19½Ã 106:36 And served their idols, Which became a snare to them.
19½Ã 106:37 They even sacrificed their sons and their daughters to the demons,
19½Ã 106:38 And shed innocent blood, The blood of their sons and their daughters, Whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan; And the land was polluted with the blood.
19½Ã 106:39 Thus they became unclean in their practices, And played the harlot in their deeds.
19½Ã 106:40 Therefore the anger of the LORD was kindled against His people, And He abhorred His inheritance.
19½Ã 106:41 Then He gave them into the hand of the nations; And those who hated them ruled over them.
19½Ã 106:42 Their enemies also oppressed them, And they were subdued under their power.
19½Ã 106:43 Many times He would deliver them; They, however, were rebellious in their counsel, And [so] sank down in their iniquity.
19½Ã 106:44 Nevertheless He looked upon their distress, When He heard their cry;
19½Ã 106:45 And He remembered His covenant for their sake, And relented according to the greatness of His lovingkindness.
19½Ã 106:46 He also made them [objects] of compassion In the presence of all their captors.
19½Ã 106:47 Save us, O LORD our God, And gather us from among the nations, To give thanks to Thy holy name, And glory in Thy praise.
19½Ã 106:48 Blessed be the LORD, the God of Israel, From everlasting even to everlasting. And let all the people say, "Amen." Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 107:1 Oh give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 107:2 Let the redeemed of the LORD say [so], Whom He has redeemed from the hand of the adversary,
19½Ã 107:3 And gathered from the lands, From the east and from the west, From the north and from the south.
19½Ã 107:4 They wandered in the wilderness in a desert region; They did not find a way to an inhabited city.
19½Ã 107:5 [They were] hungry and thirsty; Their soul fainted within them.
19½Ã 107:6 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble; He delivered them out of their distresses.
19½Ã 107:7 He led them also by a straight way, To go to an inhabited city.
19½Ã 107:8 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His lovingkindness, And for His wonders to the sons of men!
19½Ã 107:9 For He has satisfied the thirsty soul, And the hungry soul He has filled with what is good.
19½Ã 107:10 There were those who dwelt in darkness and in the shadow of death, Prisoners in misery and chains,
19½Ã 107:11 Because they had rebelled against the words of God, And spurned the counsel of the Most High.
19½Ã 107:12 Therefore He humbled their heart with labor; They stumbled and there was none to help.
19½Ã 107:13 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble; He saved them out of their distresses.
19½Ã 107:14 He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, And broke their bands apart.
19½Ã 107:15 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His lovingkindness, And for His wonders to the sons of men!
19½Ã 107:16 For He has shattered gates of bronze, And cut bars of iron asunder.
19½Ã 107:17 Fools, because of their rebellious way, And because of their iniquities, were afflicted.
19½Ã 107:18 Their soul abhorred all kinds of food; And they drew near to the gates of death.
19½Ã 107:19 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble; He saved them out of their distresses.
19½Ã 107:20 He sent His word and healed them, And delivered [them] from their destructions.
19½Ã 107:21 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His lovingkindness, And for His wonders to the sons of men!
19½Ã 107:22 Let them also offer sacrifices of thanksgiving, And tell of His works with joyful singing.
19½Ã 107:23 Those who go down to the sea in ships, Who do business on great waters;
19½Ã 107:24 They have seen the works of the LORD, And His wonders in the deep.
19½Ã 107:25 For He spoke and raised up a stormy wind, Which lifted up the waves of the sea.
19½Ã 107:26 They rose up to the heavens, they went down to the depths; Their soul melted away in [their] misery.
19½Ã 107:27 They reeled and staggered like a drunken man, And were at their wits' end.
19½Ã 107:28 Then they cried to the LORD in their trouble, And He brought them out of their distresses.
19½Ã 107:29 He caused the storm to be still, So that the waves of the sea were hushed.
19½Ã 107:30 Then they were glad because they were quiet; So He guided them to their desired haven.
19½Ã 107:31 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His lovingkindness, And for His wonders to the sons of men!
19½Ã 107:32 Let them extol Him also in the congregation of the people, And praise Him at the seat of the elders.
19½Ã 107:33 He changes rivers into a wilderness, And springs of water into a thirsty ground;
19½Ã 107:34 A fruitful land into a salt waste, Because of the wickedness of those who dwell in it.
19½Ã 107:35 He changes a wilderness into a pool of water, And a dry land into springs of water;
19½Ã 107:36 And there He makes the hungry to dwell, So that they may establish an inhabited city,
19½Ã 107:37 And sow fields, and plant vineyards, And gather a fruitful harvest.
19½Ã 107:38 Also He blesses them and they multiply greatly; And He does not let their cattle decrease.
19½Ã 107:39 When they are diminished and bowed down Through oppression, misery, and sorrow,
19½Ã 107:40 He pours contempt upon princes, And makes them wander in a pathless waste.
19½Ã 107:41 But He sets the needy securely on high away from affliction, And makes [his] families like a flock.
19½Ã 107:42 The upright see it, and are glad; But all unrighteousness shuts its mouth.
19½Ã 107:43 Who is wise? Let him give heed to these things; And consider the lovingkindnesses of the LORD.
19½Ã 108:1 {A Song, a Psalm of David.} My heart is steadfast, O God; I will sing, I will sing praises, even with my soul.
19½Ã 108:2 Awake, harp and lyre; I will awaken the dawn!
19½Ã 108:3 I will give thanks to Thee, O LORD, among the peoples; And I will sing praises to Thee among the nations.
19½Ã 108:4 For Thy lovingkindness is great above the heavens; And Thy truth [ reaches] to the skies.
19½Ã 108:5 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens, And Thy glory above all the earth.
19½Ã 108:6 That Thy beloved may be delivered, Save with Thy right hand, and answer me!
19½Ã 108:7 God has spoken in His holiness£º "I will exult, I will portion out Shechem, And measure out the valley of Succoth.
19½Ã 108:8 "Gilead is Mine, Manasseh is Mine; Ephraim also is the helmet of My head; Judah is My scepter.
19½Ã 108:9 "Moab is My washbowl; Over Edom I shall throw My shoe; Over Philistia I will shout aloud."
19½Ã 108:10 Who will bring me into the besieged city? Who will lead me to Edom?
19½Ã 108:11 Hast not Thou Thyself, O God, rejected us? And wilt Thou not go forth with our armies, O God?
19½Ã 108:12 Oh give us help against the adversary, For deliverance by man is in vain.
19½Ã 108:13 Through God we shall do valiantly; And it is He who will tread down our adversaries.
19½Ã 109:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} O God of my praise, Do not be silent!
19½Ã 109:2 For they have opened the wicked and deceitful mouth against me; They have spoken against me with a lying tongue.
19½Ã 109:3 They have also surrounded me with words of hatred, And fought against me without cause.
19½Ã 109:4 In return for my love they act as my accusers; But I am [in] prayer.
19½Ã 109:5 Thus they have repaid me evil for good, And hatred for my love.
19½Ã 109:6 Appoint a wicked man over him; And let an accuser stand at his right hand.
19½Ã 109:7 When he is judged, let him come forth guilty; And let his prayer become sin.
19½Ã 109:8 Let his days be few; Let another take his office.
19½Ã 109:9 Let his children be fatherless, And his wife a widow.
19½Ã 109:10 Let his children wander about and beg; And let them seek [sustenance] far from their ruined homes.
19½Ã 109:11 Let the creditor seize all that he has; And let strangers plunder the product of his labor.
19½Ã 109:12 Let there be none to extend lovingkindness to him, Nor any to be gracious to his fatherless children.
19½Ã 109:13 Let his posterity be cut off; In a following generation let their name be blotted out.
19½Ã 109:14 Let the iniquity of his fathers be remembered before the LORD, And do not let the sin of his mother be blotted out.
19½Ã 109:15 Let them be before the LORD continually, That He may cut off their memory from the earth;
19½Ã 109:16 Because he did not remember to show lovingkindness, But persecuted the afflicted and needy man, And the despondent in heart, to put [ them] to death.
19½Ã 109:17 He also loved cursing, so it came to him; And he did not delight in blessing, so it was far from him.
19½Ã 109:18 But he clothed himself with cursing as with his garment, And it entered into his body like water, And like oil into his bones.
19½Ã 109:19 Let it be to him as a garment with which he covers himself, And for a belt with which he constantly girds himself.
19½Ã 109:20 Let this be the reward of my accusers from the LORD, And of those who speak evil against my soul.
19½Ã 109:21 But Thou, O GOD, the Lord, deal [kindly] with me for Thy name's sake; Because Thy lovingkindness is good, deliver me;
19½Ã 109:22 For I am afflicted and needy, And my heart is wounded within me.
19½Ã 109:23 I am passing like a shadow when it lengthens; I am shaken off like the locust.
19½Ã 109:24 My knees are weak from fasting; And my flesh has grown lean, without fatness.
19½Ã 109:25 I also have become a reproach to them; When they see me, they wag their head.
19½Ã 109:26 Help me, O LORD my God; Save me according to Thy lovingkindness.
19½Ã 109:27 And let them know that this is Thy hand; Thou, LORD, hast done it.
19½Ã 109:28 Let them curse, but do Thou bless; When they arise, they shall be ashamed, But Thy servant shall be glad.
19½Ã 109:29 Let my accusers be clothed with dishonor, And let them cover themselves with their own shame as with a robe.
19½Ã 109:30 With my mouth I will give thanks abundantly to the LORD; And in the midst of many I will praise Him.
19½Ã 109:31 For He stands at the right hand of the needy, To save him from those who judge his soul.
19½Ã 110:1 {A Psalm of David.} The LORD says to my Lord£º "Sit at My right hand, Until I make Thine enemies a footstool for Thy feet."
19½Ã 110:2 The LORD will stretch forth Thy strong scepter from Zion, [saying], "Rule in the midst of Thine enemies."
19½Ã 110:3 Thy people will volunteer freely in the day of Thy power; In holy array, from the womb of the dawn, Thy youth are to Thee [as] the dew.
19½Ã 110:4 The LORD has sworn and will not change His mind, "Thou art a priest forever According to the order of Melchizedek."
19½Ã 110:5 The Lord is at Thy right hand; He will shatter kings in the day of His wrath.
19½Ã 110:6 He will judge among the nations, He will fill [them] with corpses, He will shatter the chief men over a broad country.
19½Ã 110:7 He will drink from the brook by the wayside; Therefore He will lift up [His] head.
19½Ã 111:1 Praise the LORD! I will give thanks to the LORD with all [my] heart, In the company of the upright and in the assembly.
19½Ã 111:2 Great are the works of the LORD; [They are] studied by all who delight in them.
19½Ã 111:3 Splendid and majestic is His work; And His righteousness endures forever.
19½Ã 111:4 He has made His wonders to be remembered; The LORD is gracious and compassionate.
19½Ã 111:5 He has given food to those who fear Him; He will remember His covenant forever.
19½Ã 111:6 He has made known to His people the power of His works, In giving them the heritage of the nations.
19½Ã 111:7 The works of His hands are truth and justice; All His precepts are sure.
19½Ã 111:8 They are upheld forever and ever; They are performed in truth and uprightness.
19½Ã 111:9 He has sent redemption to His people; He has ordained His covenant forever; Holy and awesome is His name.
19½Ã 111:10 The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom; A good understanding have all those who do [His commandments]; His praise endures forever.
19½Ã 112:1 Praise the LORD! How blessed is the man who fears the LORD, Who greatly delights in His commandments.
19½Ã 112:2 His descendants will be mighty on earth; The generation of the upright will be blessed.
19½Ã 112:3 Wealth and riches are in his house, And his righteousness endures forever.
19½Ã 112:4 Light arises in the darkness for the upright; [He is] gracious and compassionate and righteous.
19½Ã 112:5 It is well with the man who is gracious and lends; He will maintain his cause in judgment.
19½Ã 112:6 For he will never be shaken; The righteous will be remembered forever.
19½Ã 112:7 He will not fear evil tidings; His heart is steadfast, trusting in the LORD.
19½Ã 112:8 His heart is upheld, he will not fear, Until he looks [with satisfaction] on his adversaries.
19½Ã 112:9 He has given freely to the poor; His righteousness endures forever; His horn will be exalted in honor.
19½Ã 112:10 The wicked will see it and be vexed; He will gnash his teeth and melt away; The desire of the wicked will perish.
19½Ã 113:1 Praise the LORD! Praise, O servants of the LORD. Praise the name of the LORD.
19½Ã 113:2 Blessed be the name of the LORD From this time forth and forever.
19½Ã 113:3 From the rising of the sun to its setting The name of the LORD is to be praised.
19½Ã 113:4 The LORD is high above all nations; His glory is above the heavens.
19½Ã 113:5 Who is like the LORD our God, Who is enthroned on high,
19½Ã 113:6 Who humbles Himself to behold [The things that are] in heaven and in the earth?
19½Ã 113:7 He raises the poor from the dust, And lifts the needy from the ash heap,
19½Ã 113:8 To make [them] sit with princes, With the princes of His people.
19½Ã 113:9 He makes the barren woman abide in the house [As] a joyful mother of children. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 114:1 When Israel went forth from Egypt, The house of Jacob from a people of strange language,
19½Ã 114:2 Judah became His sanctuary, Israel, His dominion.
19½Ã 114:3 The sea looked and fled; The Jordan turned back.
19½Ã 114:4 The mountains skipped like rams, The hills, like lambs.
19½Ã 114:5 What ails you, O sea, that you flee? O Jordan, that you turn back?
19½Ã 114:6 O mountains, that you skip like rams? O hills, like lambs?
19½Ã 114:7 Tremble, O earth, before the Lord, Before the God of Jacob,
19½Ã 114:8 Who turned the rock into a pool of water, The flint into a fountain of water.
19½Ã 115:1 Not to us, O LORD, not to us, But to Thy name give glory Because of Thy lovingkindness, because of Thy truth.
19½Ã 115:2 Why should the nations say, "Where, now, is their God?"
19½Ã 115:3 But our God is in the heavens; He does whatever He pleases.
19½Ã 115:4 Their idols are silver and gold, The work of man's hands.
19½Ã 115:5 They have mouths, but they cannot speak; They have eyes, but they cannot see;
19½Ã 115:6 They have ears, but they cannot hear; They have noses, but they cannot smell;
19½Ã 115:7 They have hands, but they cannot feel; They have feet, but they cannot walk; They cannot make a sound with their throat.
19½Ã 115:8 Those who make them will become like them, Everyone who trusts in them.
19½Ã 115:9 O Israel, trust in the LORD; He is their help and their shield.
19½Ã 115:10 O house of Aaron, trust in the LORD; He is their help and their shield.
19½Ã 115:11 You who fear the LORD, trust in the LORD; He is their help and their shield.
19½Ã 115:12 The LORD has been mindful of us; He will bless [us]; He will bless the house of Israel; He will bless the house of Aaron.
19½Ã 115:13 He will bless those who fear the LORD, The small together with the great.
19½Ã 115:14 May the LORD give you increase, You and your children.
19½Ã 115:15 May you be blessed of the LORD, Maker of heaven and earth.
19½Ã 115:16 The heavens are the heavens of the LORD; But the earth He has given to the sons of men.
19½Ã 115:17 The dead do not praise the LORD, Nor [do] any who go down into silence;
19½Ã 115:18 But as for us, we will bless the LORD From this time forth and forever. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 116:1 I love the LORD, because He hears My voice [and] my supplications.
19½Ã 116:2 Because He has inclined His ear to me, Therefore I shall call [upon Him] as long as I live.
19½Ã 116:3 The cords of death encompassed me, And the terrors of Sheol came upon me; I found distress and sorrow.
19½Ã 116:4 Then I called upon the name of the LORD£º "O LORD, I beseech Thee, save my life!"
19½Ã 116:5 Gracious is the LORD, and righteous; Yes, our God is compassionate.
19½Ã 116:6 The LORD preserves the simple; I was brought low, and He saved me.
19½Ã 116:7 Return to your rest, O my soul, For the LORD has dealt bountifully with you.
19½Ã 116:8 For Thou hast rescued my soul from death, My eyes from tears, My feet from stumbling.
19½Ã 116:9 I shall walk before the LORD In the land of the living.
19½Ã 116:10 I believed when I said, "I am greatly afflicted."
19½Ã 116:11 I said in my alarm, "All men are liars."
19½Ã 116:12 What shall I render to the LORD For all His benefits toward me?
19½Ã 116:13 I shall lift up the cup of salvation, And call upon the name of the LORD.
19½Ã 116:14 I shall pay my vows to the LORD, Oh [may it be] in the presence of all His people.
19½Ã 116:15 Precious in the sight of the LORD Is the death of His godly ones.
19½Ã 116:16 O LORD, surely I am Thy servant, I am Thy servant, the son of Thy handmaid, Thou hast loosed my bonds.
19½Ã 116:17 To Thee I shall offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving, And call upon the name of the LORD.
19½Ã 116:18 I shall pay my vows to the LORD, Oh [may it be] in the presence of all His people,
19½Ã 116:19 In the courts of the Lord's house, In the midst of you, O Jerusalem. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 117:1 Praise the LORD, all nations; Laud Him, all peoples!
19½Ã 117:2 For His lovingkindness is great toward us, And the truth of the LORD is everlasting. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 118:1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 118:2 Oh let Israel say, "His lovingkindness is everlasting."
19½Ã 118:3 Oh let the house of Aaron say, "His lovingkindness is everlasting."
19½Ã 118:4 Oh let those who fear the LORD say, "His lovingkindness is everlasting."
19½Ã 118:5 From [my] distress I called upon the LORD; The LORD answered me [and set me] in a large place.
19½Ã 118:6 The LORD is for me; I will not fear; What can man do to me?
19½Ã 118:7 The LORD is for me among those who help me; Therefore I shall look [with satisfaction] on those who hate me.
19½Ã 118:8 It is better to take refuge in the LORD Than to trust in man.
19½Ã 118:9 It is better to take refuge in the LORD Than to trust in princes.
19½Ã 118:10 All nations surrounded me; In the name of the LORD I will surely cut them off.
19½Ã 118:11 They surrounded me, yes, they surrounded me; In the name of the LORD I will surely cut them off.
19½Ã 118:12 They surrounded me like bees; They were extinguished as a fire of thorns; In the name of the LORD I will surely cut them off.
19½Ã 118:13 You pushed me violently so that I was falling, But the LORD helped me.
19½Ã 118:14 The LORD is my strength and song, And He has become my salvation.
19½Ã 118:15 The sound of joyful shouting and salvation is in the tents of the righteous; The right hand of the LORD does valiantly.
19½Ã 118:16 The right hand of the LORD is exalted; The right hand of the LORD does valiantly.
19½Ã 118:17 I shall not die, but live, And tell of the works of the LORD.
19½Ã 118:18 The LORD has disciplined me severely, But He has not given me over to death.
19½Ã 118:19 Open to me the gates of righteousness; I shall enter through them, I shall give thanks to the LORD.
19½Ã 118:20 This is the gate of the LORD; The righteous will enter through it.
19½Ã 118:21 I shall give thanks to Thee, for Thou hast answered me; And Thou hast become my salvation.
19½Ã 118:22 The stone which the builders rejected Has become the chief corner [stone.]
19½Ã 118:23 This is the Lord's doing; It is marvelous in our eyes.
19½Ã 118:24 This is the day which the LORD has made; Let us rejoice and be glad in it.
19½Ã 118:25 O LORD, do save, we beseech Thee; O LORD, we beseech Thee, do send prosperity!
19½Ã 118:26 Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the LORD; We have blessed you from the house of the LORD.
19½Ã 118:27 The LORD is God, and He has given us light; Bind the festival sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar.
19½Ã 118:28 Thou art my God, and I give thanks to Thee; [Thou art] my God, I extol Thee.
19½Ã 118:29 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 119:1 How blessed are those whose way is blameless, Who walk in the law of the LORD.
19½Ã 119:2 How blessed are those who observe His testimonies, Who seek Him with all [their] heart.
19½Ã 119:3 They also do no unrighteousness; They walk in His ways.
19½Ã 119:4 Thou hast ordained Thy precepts, That we should keep [them] diligently.
19½Ã 119:5 Oh that my ways may be established To keep Thy statutes!
19½Ã 119:6 Then I shall not be ashamed When I look upon all Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:7 I shall give thanks to Thee with uprightness of heart, When I learn Thy righteous judgments.
19½Ã 119:8 I shall keep Thy statutes; Do not forsake me utterly!
19½Ã 119:9 How can a young man keep his way pure? By keeping [it] according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:10 With all my heart I have sought Thee; Do not let me wander from Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:11 Thy word I have treasured in my heart, That I may not sin against Thee.
19½Ã 119:12 Blessed art Thou, O LORD; Teach me Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:13 With my lips I have told of All the ordinances of Thy mouth.
19½Ã 119:14 I have rejoiced in the way of Thy testimonies, As much as in all riches.
19½Ã 119:15 I will meditate on Thy precepts, And regard Thy ways.
19½Ã 119:16 I shall delight in Thy statutes; I shall not forget Thy word.
19½Ã 119:17 Deal bountifully with Thy servant, That I may live and keep Thy word.
19½Ã 119:18 Open my eyes, that I may behold Wonderful things from Thy law.
19½Ã 119:19 I am a stranger in the earth; Do not hide Thy commandments from me.
19½Ã 119:20 My soul is crushed with longing After Thine ordinances at all times.
19½Ã 119:21 Thou dost rebuke the arrogant, the cursed, Who wander from Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:22 Take away reproach and contempt from me, For I observe Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:23 Even though princes sit and talk against me, Thy servant meditates on Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:24 Thy testimonies also are my delight; [They are] my counselors.
19½Ã 119:25 My soul cleaves to the dust; Revive me according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:26 I have told of my ways, and Thou hast answered me; Teach me Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:27 Make me understand the way of Thy precepts, So I will meditate on Thy wonders.
19½Ã 119:28 My soul weeps because of grief; Strengthen me according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:29 Remove the false way from me, And graciously grant me Thy law.
19½Ã 119:30 I have chosen the faithful way; I have placed Thine ordinances [before me.]
19½Ã 119:31 I cleave to Thy testimonies; O LORD, do not put me to shame!
19½Ã 119:32 I shall run the way of Thy commandments, For Thou wilt enlarge my heart.
19½Ã 119:33 Teach me, O LORD, the way of Thy statutes, And I shall observe it to the end.
19½Ã 119:34 Give me understanding, that I may observe Thy law, And keep it with all [my] heart.
19½Ã 119:35 Make me walk in the path of Thy commandments, For I delight in it.
19½Ã 119:36 Incline my heart to Thy testimonies, And not to [dishonest] gain.
19½Ã 119:37 Turn away my eyes from looking at vanity, And revive me in Thy ways.
19½Ã 119:38 Establish Thy word to Thy servant, As that which produces reverence for Thee.
19½Ã 119:39 Turn away my reproach which I dread, For Thine ordinances are good.
19½Ã 119:40 Behold, I long for Thy precepts; Revive me through Thy righteousness.
19½Ã 119:41 May Thy lovingkindnesses also come to me, O LORD, Thy salvation according to Thy word;
19½Ã 119:42 So I shall have an answer for him who reproaches me, For I trust in Thy word.
19½Ã 119:43 And do not take the word of truth utterly out of my mouth, For I wait for Thine ordinances.
19½Ã 119:44 So I will keep Thy law continually, Forever and ever.
19½Ã 119:45 And I will walk at liberty, For I seek Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:46 I will also speak of Thy testimonies before kings, And shall not be ashamed.
19½Ã 119:47 And I shall delight in Thy commandments, Which I love.
19½Ã 119:48 And I shall lift up my hands to Thy commandments, Which I love; And I will meditate on Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:49 Remember the word to Thy servant, In which Thou hast made me hope.
19½Ã 119:50 This is my comfort in my affliction, That Thy word has revived me.
19½Ã 119:51 The arrogant utterly deride me, [Yet] I do not turn aside from Thy law.
19½Ã 119:52 I have remembered Thine ordinances from of old, O LORD, And comfort myself.
19½Ã 119:53 Burning indignation has seized me because of the wicked, Who forsake Thy law.
19½Ã 119:54 Thy statutes are my songs In the house of my pilgrimage.
19½Ã 119:55 O LORD, I remember Thy name in the night, And keep Thy law.
19½Ã 119:56 This has become mine, That I observe Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:57 The LORD is my portion; I have promised to keep Thy words.
19½Ã 119:58 I entreated Thy favor with all [my] heart; Be gracious to me according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:59 I considered my ways, And turned my feet to Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:60 I hastened and did not delay To keep Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:61 The cords of the wicked have encircled me, [But] I have not forgotten Thy law.
19½Ã 119:62 At midnight I shall rise to give thanks to Thee Because of Thy righteous ordinances.
19½Ã 119:63 I am a companion of all those who fear Thee, And of those who keep Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:64 The earth is full of Thy lovingkindness, O LORD; Teach me Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:65 Thou hast dealt well with Thy servant, O LORD, according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:66 Teach me good discernment and knowledge, For I believe in Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:67 Before I was afflicted I went astray, But now I keep Thy word.
19½Ã 119:68 Thou art good and doest good; Teach me Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:69 The arrogant have forged a lie against me; With all [my] heart I will observe Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:70 Their heart is covered with fat, [But] I delight in Thy law.
19½Ã 119:71 It is good for me that I was afflicted, That I may learn Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:72 The law of Thy mouth is better to me Than thousands of gold and silver [pieces].
19½Ã 119:73 Thy hands made me and fashioned me; Give me understanding, that I may learn Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:74 May those who fear Thee see me and be glad, Because I wait for Thy word.
19½Ã 119:75 I know, O LORD, that Thy judgments are righteous, And that in faithfulness Thou hast afflicted me.
19½Ã 119:76 O may Thy lovingkindness comfort me, According to Thy word to Thy servant.
19½Ã 119:77 May Thy compassion come to me that I may live, For Thy law is my delight.
19½Ã 119:78 May the arrogant be ashamed, for they subvert me with a lie; [But] I shall meditate on Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:79 May those who fear Thee turn to me, Even those who know Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:80 May my heart be blameless in Thy statutes, That I may not be ashamed.
19½Ã 119:81 My soul languishes for Thy salvation; I wait for Thy word.
19½Ã 119:82 My eyes fail [with longing] for Thy word, While I say, "When wilt Thou comfort me?"
19½Ã 119:83 Though I have become like a wineskin in the smoke, I do not forget Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:84 How many are the days of Thy servant? When wilt Thou execute judgment on those who persecute me?
19½Ã 119:85 The arrogant have dug pits for me, [Men] who are not in accord with Thy law.
19½Ã 119:86 All Thy commandments are faithful; They have persecuted me with a lie; help me!
19½Ã 119:87 They almost destroyed me on earth, But as for me, I did not forsake Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:88 Revive me according to Thy lovingkindness, So that I may keep the testimony of Thy mouth.
19½Ã 119:89 Forever, O LORD, Thy word is settled in heaven.
19½Ã 119:90 Thy faithfulness [continues] throughout all generations; Thou didst establish the earth, and it stands.
19½Ã 119:91 They stand this day according to Thine ordinances, For all things are Thy servants.
19½Ã 119:92 If Thy law had not been my delight, Then I would have perished in my affliction.
19½Ã 119:93 I will never forget Thy precepts, For by them Thou hast revived me.
19½Ã 119:94 I am Thine, save me; For I have sought Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:95 The wicked wait for me to destroy me; I shall diligently consider Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:96 I have seen a limit to all perfection; Thy commandment is exceedingly broad.
19½Ã 119:97 O how I love Thy law! It is my meditation all the day.
19½Ã 119:98 Thy commandments make me wiser than my enemies, For they are ever mine.
19½Ã 119:99 I have more insight than all my teachers, For Thy testimonies are my meditation.
19½Ã 119:100 I understand more than the aged, Because I have observed Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:101 I have restrained my feet from every evil way, That I may keep Thy word.
19½Ã 119:102 I have not turned aside from Thine ordinances, For Thou Thyself hast taught me.
19½Ã 119:103 How sweet are Thy words to my taste! [Yes, sweeter] than honey to my mouth!
19½Ã 119:104 From Thy precepts I get understanding; Therefore I hate every false way.
19½Ã 119:105 Thy word is a lamp to my feet, And a light to my path.
19½Ã 119:106 I have sworn, and I will confirm it, That I will keep Thy righteous ordinances.
19½Ã 119:107 I am exceedingly afflicted; Revive me, O LORD, according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:108 O accept the freewill offerings of my mouth, O LORD, And teach me Thine ordinances.
19½Ã 119:109 My life is continually in my hand, Yet I do not forget Thy law.
19½Ã 119:110 The wicked have laid a snare for me, Yet I have not gone astray from Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:111 I have inherited Thy testimonies forever, For they are the joy of my heart.
19½Ã 119:112 I have inclined my heart to perform Thy statutes Forever, [even] to the end.
19½Ã 119:113 I hate those who are double-minded, But I love Thy law.
19½Ã 119:114 Thou art my hiding place and my shield; I wait for Thy word.
19½Ã 119:115 Depart from me, evildoers, That I may observe the commandments of my God.
19½Ã 119:116 Sustain me according to Thy word, that I may live; And do not let me be ashamed of my hope.
19½Ã 119:117 Uphold me that I may be safe, That I may have regard for Thy statutes continually.
19½Ã 119:118 Thou hast rejected all those who wander from Thy statutes, For their deceitfulness is useless.
19½Ã 119:119 Thou hast removed all the wicked of the earth [like] dross; Therefore I love Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:120 My flesh trembles for fear of Thee, And I am afraid of Thy judgments.
19½Ã 119:121 I have done justice and righteousness; Do not leave me to my oppressors.
19½Ã 119:122 Be surety for Thy servant for good; Do not let the arrogant oppress me.
19½Ã 119:123 My eyes fail [with longing] for Thy salvation, And for Thy righteous word.
19½Ã 119:124 Deal with Thy servant according to Thy lovingkindness, And teach me Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:125 I am Thy servant; give me understanding, That I may know Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:126 It is time for the LORD to act, [For] they have broken Thy law.
19½Ã 119:127 Therefore I love Thy commandments Above gold, yes, above fine gold.
19½Ã 119:128 Therefore I esteem right all [Thy] precepts concerning everything, I hate every false way.
19½Ã 119:129 Thy testimonies are wonderful; Therefore my soul observes them.
19½Ã 119:130 The unfolding of Thy words gives light; It gives understanding to the simple.
19½Ã 119:131 I opened my mouth wide and panted, For I longed for Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:132 Turn to me and be gracious to me, After Thy manner with those who love Thy name.
19½Ã 119:133 Establish my footsteps in Thy word, And do not let any iniquity have dominion over me.
19½Ã 119:134 Redeem me from the oppression of man, That I may keep Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:135 Make Thy face shine upon Thy servant, And teach me Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:136 My eyes shed streams of water, Because they do not keep Thy law.
19½Ã 119:137 Righteous art Thou, O LORD, And upright are Thy judgments.
19½Ã 119:138 Thou hast commanded Thy testimonies in righteousness And exceeding faithfulness.
19½Ã 119:139 My zeal has consumed me, Because my adversaries have forgotten Thy words.
19½Ã 119:140 Thy word is very pure, Therefore Thy servant loves it.
19½Ã 119:141 I am small and despised, [Yet] I do not forget Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:142 Thy righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, And Thy law is truth.
19½Ã 119:143 Trouble and anguish have come upon me; [Yet] Thy commandments are my delight.
19½Ã 119:144 Thy testimonies are righteous forever; Give me understanding that I may live.
19½Ã 119:145 I cried with all my heart; answer me, O LORD! I will observe Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:146 I cried to Thee; save me, And I shall keep Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:147 I rise before dawn and cry for help; I wait for Thy words.
19½Ã 119:148 My eyes anticipate the night watches, That I may meditate on Thy word.
19½Ã 119:149 Hear my voice according to Thy lovingkindness; Revive me, O LORD, according to Thine ordinances.
19½Ã 119:150 Those who follow after wickedness draw near; They are far from Thy law.
19½Ã 119:151 Thou art near, O LORD, And all Thy commandments are truth.
19½Ã 119:152 Of old I have known from Thy testimonies, That Thou hast founded them forever.
19½Ã 119:153 Look upon my affliction and rescue me, For I do not forget Thy law.
19½Ã 119:154 Plead my cause and redeem me; Revive me according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:155 Salvation is far from the wicked, For they do not seek Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:156 Great are Thy mercies, O LORD; Revive me according to Thine ordinances.
19½Ã 119:157 Many are my persecutors and my adversaries, [Yet] I do not turn aside from Thy testimonies.
19½Ã 119:158 I behold the treacherous and loathe [them], Because they do not keep Thy word.
19½Ã 119:159 Consider how I love Thy precepts; Revive me, O LORD, according to Thy lovingkindness.
19½Ã 119:160 The sum of Thy word is truth, And every one of Thy righteous ordinances is everlasting.
19½Ã 119:161 Princes persecute me without cause, But my heart stands in awe of Thy words.
19½Ã 119:162 I rejoice at Thy word, As one who finds great spoil.
19½Ã 119:163 I hate and despise falsehood, [But] I love Thy law.
19½Ã 119:164 Seven times a day I praise Thee, Because of Thy righteous ordinances.
19½Ã 119:165 Those who love Thy law have great peace, And nothing causes them to stumble.
19½Ã 119:166 I hope for Thy salvation, O LORD, And do Thy commandments.
19½Ã 119:167 My soul keeps Thy testimonies, And I love them exceedingly.
19½Ã 119:168 I keep Thy precepts and Thy testimonies, For all my ways are before Thee.
19½Ã 119:169 Let my cry come before Thee, O LORD; Give me understanding according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:170 Let my supplication come before Thee; Deliver me according to Thy word.
19½Ã 119:171 Let my lips utter praise, For Thou dost teach me Thy statutes.
19½Ã 119:172 Let my tongue sing of Thy word, For all Thy commandments are righteousness.
19½Ã 119:173 Let Thy hand be ready to help me, For I have chosen Thy precepts.
19½Ã 119:174 I long for Thy salvation, O LORD, And Thy law is my delight.
19½Ã 119:175 Let my soul live that it may praise Thee, And let Thine ordinances help me.
19½Ã 119:176 I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek Thy servant, For I do not forget Thy commandments.
19½Ã 120:1 {A Song of Ascents.} In my trouble I cried to the LORD, And He answered me.
19½Ã 120:2 Deliver my soul, O LORD, from lying lips, From a deceitful tongue.
19½Ã 120:3 What shall be given to you, and what more shall be done to you, You deceitful tongue?
19½Ã 120:4 Sharp arrows of the warrior, With the [burning] coals of the broom tree.
19½Ã 120:5 Woe is me, for I sojourn in Meshech, For I dwell among the tents of Kedar!
19½Ã 120:6 Too long has my soul had its dwelling With those who hate peace.
19½Ã 120:7 I am [for] peace, but when I speak, They are for war.
19½Ã 121:1 {A Song of Ascents.} I Will lift up my eyes to the mountains; From whence shall my help come?
19½Ã 121:2 My help [comes] from the LORD, Who made heaven and earth.
19½Ã 121:3 He will not allow your foot to slip; He who keeps you will not slumber.
19½Ã 121:4 Behold, He who keeps Israel Will neither slumber nor sleep.
19½Ã 121:5 The LORD is your keeper; The LORD is your shade on your right hand.
19½Ã 121:6 The sun will not smite you by day, Nor the moon by night.
19½Ã 121:7 The LORD will protect you from all evil; He will keep your soul.
19½Ã 121:8 The LORD will guard your going out and your coming in From this time forth and forever.
19½Ã 122:1 {A Song of Ascents, of David.} I was glad when they said to me, "Let us go to the house of the LORD."
19½Ã 122:2 Our feet are standing Within your gates, O Jerusalem,
19½Ã 122:3 Jerusalem, that is built As a city that is compact together;
19½Ã 122:4 To which the tribes go up, even the tribes of the LORD-- An ordinance for Israel-- To give thanks to the name of the LORD.
19½Ã 122:5 For there thrones were set for judgment, The thrones of the house of David.
19½Ã 122:6 Pray for the peace of Jerusalem£º "May they prosper who love you.
19½Ã 122:7 "May peace be within your walls, And prosperity within your palaces."
19½Ã 122:8 For the sake of my brothers and my friends, I will now say, "May peace be within you."
19½Ã 122:9 For the sake of the house of the LORD our God I will seek your good.
19½Ã 123:1 {A Song of Ascents.} To Thee I lift up my eyes, O Thou who art enthroned in the heavens!
19½Ã 123:2 Behold, as the eyes of servants [look] to the hand of their master, As the eyes of a maid to the hand of her mistress; So our eyes [look] to the LORD our God, Until He shall be gracious to us.
19½Ã 123:3 Be gracious to us, O LORD, be gracious to us; For we are greatly filled with contempt.
19½Ã 123:4 Our soul is greatly filled With the scoffing of those who are at ease, [And] with the contempt of the proud.
19½Ã 124:1 {A Song of Ascents, of David.} "Had it not been the LORD who was on our side," Let Israel now say,
19½Ã 124:2 "Had it not been the LORD who was on our side, When men rose up against us;
19½Ã 124:3 Then they would have swallowed us alive, When their anger was kindled against us;
19½Ã 124:4 Then the waters would have engulfed us, The stream would have swept over our soul;
19½Ã 124:5 Then the raging waters would have swept over our soul. "
19½Ã 124:6 Blessed be the LORD, Who has not given us to be torn by their teeth.
19½Ã 124:7 Our soul has escaped as a bird out of the snare of the trapper; The snare is broken and we have escaped.
19½Ã 124:8 Our help is in the name of the LORD, Who made heaven and earth.
19½Ã 125:1 {A Song of Ascents.} Those who trust in the LORD Are as Mount Zion, which cannot be moved, but abides forever.
19½Ã 125:2 As the mountains surround Jerusalem, So the LORD surrounds His people From this time forth and forever.
19½Ã 125:3 For the scepter of wickedness shall not rest upon the land of the righteous; That the righteous may not put forth their hands to do wrong.
19½Ã 125:4 Do good, O LORD, to those who are good, And to those who are upright in their hearts.
19½Ã 125:5 But as for those who turn aside to their crooked ways, The LORD will lead them away with the doers of iniquity. Peace be upon Israel.
19½Ã 126:1 {A Song of Ascents.} When the LORD brought back the captive ones of Zion, We were like those who dream.
19½Ã 126:2 Then our mouth was filled with laughter, And our tongue with joyful shouting; Then they said among the nations, "The LORD has done great things for them."
19½Ã 126:3 The LORD has done great things for us; We are glad.
19½Ã 126:4 Restore our captivity, O LORD, As the streams in the South.
19½Ã 126:5 Those who sow in tears shall reap with joyful shouting.
19½Ã 126:6 He who goes to and fro weeping, carrying [his] bag of seed, Shall indeed come again with a shout of joy, bringing his sheaves [with him].
19½Ã 127:1 {A Song of Ascents, of Solomon.} Unless the LORD builds the house, They labor in vain who build it; Unless the LORD guards the city, The watchman keeps awake in vain.
19½Ã 127:2 It is vain for you to rise up early, To retire late, To eat the bread of painful labors; For He gives to His beloved [even in his] sleep.
19½Ã 127:3 Behold, children are a gift of the LORD; The fruit of the womb is a reward.
19½Ã 127:4 Like arrows in the hand of a warrior, So are the children of one's youth.
19½Ã 127:5 How blessed is the man whose quiver is full of them; They shall not be ashamed, When they speak with their enemies in the gate.
19½Ã 128:1 {A Song of Ascents.} How blessed is everyone who fears the LORD, Who walks in His ways.
19½Ã 128:2 When you shall eat of the fruit of your hands, You will be happy and it will be well with you.
19½Ã 128:3 Your wife shall be like a fruitful vine, Within your house, Your children like olive plants Around your table.
19½Ã 128:4 Behold, for thus shall the man be blessed Who fears the LORD.
19½Ã 128:5 The LORD bless you from Zion, And may you see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of your life.
19½Ã 128:6 Indeed, may you see your children's children. Peace be upon Israel!
19½Ã 129:1 {A Song of Ascents.} "Many times they have persecuted me from my youth up," Let Israel now say,
19½Ã 129:2 "Many times they have persecuted me from my youth up; Yet they have not prevailed against me.
19½Ã 129:3 "The plowers plowed upon my back; They lengthened their furrows."
19½Ã 129:4 The LORD is righteous; He has cut in two the cords of the wicked.
19½Ã 129:5 May all who hate Zion, Be put to shame and turned backward,
19½Ã 129:6 Let them be like grass upon the housetops, Which withers before it grows up;
19½Ã 129:7 With which the reaper does not fill his hand, Or the binder of sheaves his bosom;
19½Ã 129:8 Nor do those who pass by say, "The blessing of the LORD be upon you; We bless you in the name of the LORD."
19½Ã 130:1 {A Song of Ascents.} Out of the depths I have cried to Thee, O LORD.
19½Ã 130:2 Lord, hear my voice! Let Thine ears be attentive To the voice of my supplications.
19½Ã 130:3 If Thou, LORD, shouldst mark iniquities, O Lord, who could stand?
19½Ã 130:4 But there is forgiveness with Thee, That Thou mayest be feared.
19½Ã 130:5 I wait for the LORD, my soul does wait, And in His word do I hope.
19½Ã 130:6 My soul [waits] for the Lord More than the watchmen for the morning; [Indeed, more than] the watchmen for the morning.
19½Ã 130:7 O Israel, hope in the LORD; For with the LORD there is lovingkindness, And with Him is abundant redemption.
19½Ã 130:8 And He will redeem Israel From all his iniquities.
19½Ã 131:1 {A Song of Ascents, of David.} O LORD, my heart is not proud, nor my eyes haughty; Nor do I involve myself in great matters, Or in things too difficult for me.
19½Ã 131:2 Surely I have composed and quieted my soul; Like a weaned child [rests] against his mother, My soul is like a weaned child within me.
19½Ã 131:3 O Israel, hope in the LORD From this time forth and forever.
19½Ã 132:1 {A Song of Ascents.} Remember, O LORD, on David's behalf, All his affliction;
19½Ã 132:2 How he swore to the LORD, And vowed to the Mighty One of Jacob,
19½Ã 132:3 "Surely I will not enter my house, Nor lie on my bed;
19½Ã 132:4 I will not give sleep to my eyes, Or slumber to my eyelids;
19½Ã 132:5 Until I find a place for the LORD, A dwelling place for the Mighty One of Jacob. "
19½Ã 132:6 Behold, we heard of it in Ephrathah; We found it in the field of Jaar.
19½Ã 132:7 Let us go into His dwelling place; Let us worship at His footstool.
19½Ã 132:8 Arise, O LORD, to Thy resting place; Thou and the ark of Thy strength.
19½Ã 132:9 Let Thy priests be clothed with righteousness; And let Thy godly ones sing for joy.
19½Ã 132:10 For the sake of David Thy servant, Do not turn away the face of Thine anointed.
19½Ã 132:11 The LORD has sworn to David, A truth from which He will not turn back; "Of the fruit of your body I will set upon your throne.
19½Ã 132:12 "If your sons will keep My covenant, And My testimony which I will teach them, Their sons also shall sit upon your throne forever."
19½Ã 132:13 For the LORD has chosen Zion; He has desired it for His habitation.
19½Ã 132:14 "This is My resting place forever; Here I will dwell, for I have desired it.
19½Ã 132:15 "I will abundantly bless her provision; I will satisfy her needy with bread.
19½Ã 132:16 "Her priests also I will clothe with salvation; And her godly ones will sing aloud for joy.
19½Ã 132:17 "There I will cause the horn of David to spring forth; I have prepared a lamp for Mine anointed.
19½Ã 132:18 "His enemies I will clothe with shame; But upon himself his crown shall shine."
19½Ã 133:1 {A Song of Ascents, of David.} Behold, how good and how pleasant it is For brothers to dwell together in unity!
19½Ã 133:2 It is like the precious oil upon the head, Coming down upon the beard, [Even] Aaron's beard, Coming down upon the edge of his robes.
19½Ã 133:3 It is like the dew of Hermon, Coming down upon the mountains of Zion; For there the LORD commanded the blessing-- life forever.
19½Ã 134:1 {A Song of Ascents.} Behold, bless the LORD, all servants of the LORD, Who serve by night in the house of the LORD!
19½Ã 134:2 Lift up your hands to the sanctuary, And bless the LORD.
19½Ã 134:3 May the LORD bless you from Zion, He who made heaven and earth.
19½Ã 135:1 Praise the LORD! Praise the name of the LORD; Praise HIM, O servants of the LORD,
19½Ã 135:2 You who stand in the house of the LORD, In the courts of the house of our God!
19½Ã 135:3 Praise the LORD, for the LORD is good; Sing praises to His name, for it is lovely.
19½Ã 135:4 For the LORD has chosen Jacob for Himself, Israel for His own possession.
19½Ã 135:5 For I know that the LORD is great, And that our Lord is above all gods.
19½Ã 135:6 Whatever the LORD pleases, He does, In heaven and in earth, in the seas and in all deeps.
19½Ã 135:7 He causes the vapors to ascend from the ends of the earth; Who makes lightnings for the rain; Who brings forth the wind from His treasuries.
19½Ã 135:8 He smote the first-born of Egypt, Both of man and beast.
19½Ã 135:9 He sent signs and wonders into your midst, O Egypt, Upon Pharaoh and all his servants.
19½Ã 135:10 He smote many nations, And slew mighty kings,
19½Ã 135:11 Sihon, king of the Amorites, And Og, king of Bashan, And all the kingdoms of Canaan;
19½Ã 135:12 And He gave their land as a heritage, A heritage to Israel His people.
19½Ã 135:13 Thy name, O LORD, is everlasting, Thy remembrance, O LORD, throughout all generations.
19½Ã 135:14 For the LORD will judge His people, And will have compassion on His servants.
19½Ã 135:15 The idols of the nations are [but] silver and gold, The work of man's hands.
19½Ã 135:16 They have mouths, but they do not speak; They have eyes, but they do not see;
19½Ã 135:17 They have ears, but they do not hear; Nor is there any breath at all in their mouths.
19½Ã 135:18 Those who make them will be like them, [Yes,] everyone who trusts in them.
19½Ã 135:19 O house of Israel, bless the LORD; O house of Aaron, bless the LORD;
19½Ã 135:20 O house of Levi, bless the LORD; You who revere the LORD, bless the LORD.
19½Ã 135:21 Blessed be the LORD from Zion, Who dwells in Jerusalem. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 136:1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 136:2 Give thanks to the God of gods, For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 136:3 Give thanks to the Lord of lords, For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 136:4 To Him who alone does great wonders, For His lovingkindness is everlasting;
19½Ã 136:5 To Him who made the heavens with skill, For His lovingkindness is everlasting;
19½Ã 136:6 To Him who spread out the earth above the waters, For His lovingkindness is everlasting;
19½Ã 136:7 To Him who made [the] great lights, For His lovingkindness is everlasting£º
19½Ã 136:8 The sun to rule by day, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:9 The moon and stars to rule by night, For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 136:10 To Him who smote the Egyptians in their first-born, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:11 And brought Israel out from their midst, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:12 With a strong hand and an outstretched arm, For His lovingkindness is everlasting;
19½Ã 136:13 To Him who divided the Red Sea asunder, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:14 And made Israel pass through the midst of it, For His lovingkindness is everlasting;
19½Ã 136:15 But He overthrew Pharaoh and his army in the Red Sea, For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 136:16 To Him who led His people through the wilderness, For His lovingkindness is everlasting;
19½Ã 136:17 To Him who smote great kings, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:18 And slew mighty kings, For His lovingkindness is everlasting£º
19½Ã 136:19 Sihon, king of the Amorites, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:20 And Og, king of Bashan, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:21 And gave their land as a heritage, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:22 Even a heritage to Israel His servant, For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 136:23 Who remembered us in our low estate, For His lovingkindness is everlasting,
19½Ã 136:24 And has rescued us from our adversaries, For His lovingkindness is everlasting;
19½Ã 136:25 Who gives food to all flesh, For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 136:26 Give thanks to the God of heaven, For His lovingkindness is everlasting.
19½Ã 137:1 By the rivers of Babylon, There we sat down and wept, When we remembered Zion.
19½Ã 137:2 Upon the willows in the midst of it We hung our harps.
19½Ã 137:3 For there our captors demanded of us songs, And our tormentors mirth, [saying], "Sing us one of the songs of Zion."
19½Ã 137:4 How can we sing the Lord's song In a foreign land?
19½Ã 137:5 If I forget you, O Jerusalem, May my right hand forget [her skill.]
19½Ã 137:6 May my tongue cleave to the roof of my mouth, If I do not remember you, If I do not exalt Jerusalem Above my chief joy.
19½Ã 137:7 Remember, O LORD, against the sons of Edom The day of Jerusalem, Who said, "Raze it, raze it, To its very foundation."
19½Ã 137:8 O daughter of Babylon, you devastated one, How blessed will be the one who repays you With the recompense with which you have repaid us.
19½Ã 137:9 How blessed will be the one who seizes and dashes your little ones Against the rock.
19½Ã 138:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} I will give Thee thanks with all my heart; I will sing praises to Thee before the gods.
19½Ã 138:2 I will bow down toward Thy holy temple, And give thanks to Thy name for Thy lovingkindness and Thy truth; For Thou hast magnified Thy word according to all Thy name.
19½Ã 138:3 On the day I called Thou didst answer me; Thou didst make me bold with strength in my soul.
19½Ã 138:4 All the kings of the earth will give thanks to Thee, O LORD, When they have heard the words of Thy mouth.
19½Ã 138:5 And they will sing of the ways of the LORD. For great is the glory of the LORD.
19½Ã 138:6 For though the LORD is exalted, Yet He regards the lowly; But the haughty He knows from afar.
19½Ã 138:7 Though I walk in the midst of trouble, Thou wilt revive me; Thou wilt stretch forth Thy hand against the wrath of my enemies, And Thy right hand will save me.
19½Ã 138:8 The LORD will accomplish what concerns me; Thy lovingkindness, O LORD, is everlasting; Do not forsake the works of Thy hands.
19½Ã 139:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} O LORD, Thou hast searched me and known [me.]
19½Ã 139:2 Thou dost know when I sit down and when I rise up; Thou dost understand my thought from afar.
19½Ã 139:3 Thou dost scrutinize my path and my lying down, And art intimately acquainted with all my ways.
19½Ã 139:4 Even before there is a word on my tongue, Behold, O LORD, Thou dost know it all.
19½Ã 139:5 Thou hast enclosed me behind and before, And laid Thy hand upon me.
19½Ã 139:6 [Such] knowledge is too wonderful for me; It is [too] high, I cannot attain to it.
19½Ã 139:7 Where can I go from Thy Spirit? Or where can I flee from Thy presence?
19½Ã 139:8 If I ascend to heaven, Thou art there; If I make my bed in Sheol, behold, Thou art there.
19½Ã 139:9 If I take the wings of the dawn, If I dwell in the remotest part of the sea,
19½Ã 139:10 Even there Thy hand will lead me, And Thy right hand will lay hold of me.
19½Ã 139:11 If I say, "Surely the darkness will overwhelm me, And the light around me will be night,"
19½Ã 139:12 Even the darkness is not dark to Thee, And the night is as bright as the day. Darkness and light are alike [to Thee.]
19½Ã 139:13 For Thou didst form my inward parts; Thou didst weave me in my mother's womb.
19½Ã 139:14 I will give thanks to Thee, for I am fearfully and wonderfully made; Wonderful are Thy works, And my soul knows it very well.
19½Ã 139:15 My frame was not hidden from Thee, When I was made in secret, [And] skillfully wrought in the depths of the earth.
19½Ã 139:16 Thine eyes have seen my unformed substance; And in Thy book they were all written, The days that were ordained [for me], When as yet there was not one of them.
19½Ã 139:17 How precious also are Thy thoughts to me, O God! How vast is the sum of them!
19½Ã 139:18 If I should count them, they would outnumber the sand. When I awake, I am still with Thee.
19½Ã 139:19 O that Thou wouldst slay the wicked, O God; Depart from me, therefore, men of bloodshed.
19½Ã 139:20 For they speak against Thee wickedly, And Thine enemies take [Thy name] in vain.
19½Ã 139:21 Do I not hate those who hate Thee, O LORD? And do I not loathe those who rise up against Thee?
19½Ã 139:22 I hate them with the utmost hatred; They have become my enemies.
19½Ã 139:23 Search me, O God, and know my heart; Try me and know my anxious thoughts;
19½Ã 139:24 And see if there be any hurtful way in me, And lead me in the everlasting way.
19½Ã 140:1 {For the choir director. A Psalm of David.} Rescue me, O LORD, from evil men; Preserve me from violent men,
19½Ã 140:2 Who devise evil things in [their] hearts; They continually stir up wars.
19½Ã 140:3 They sharpen their tongues as a serpent; Poison of a viper is under their lips. Selah.
19½Ã 140:4 Keep me, O LORD, from the hands of the wicked; Preserve me from violent men, Who have purposed to trip up my feet.
19½Ã 140:5 The proud have hidden a trap for me, and cords; They have spread a net by the wayside; They have set snares for me. Selah.
19½Ã 140:6 I said to the LORD, "Thou art my God; Give ear, O LORD, to the voice of my supplications.
19½Ã 140:7 "O GOD the Lord, the strength of my salvation, Thou hast covered my head in the day of battle.
19½Ã 140:8 "Do not grant, O LORD, the desires of the wicked; Do not promote his [evil] device, [lest] they be exalted. Selah.
19½Ã 140:9 "As for the head of those who surround me, May the mischief of their lips cover them.
19½Ã 140:10 "May burning coals fall upon them; May they be cast into the fire, Into deep pits from which they cannot rise.
19½Ã 140:11 "May a slanderer not be established in the earth; May evil hunt the violent man speedily."
19½Ã 140:12 I know that the LORD will maintain the cause of the afflicted, And justice for the poor.
19½Ã 140:13 Surely the righteous will give thanks to Thy name; The upright will dwell in Thy presence.
19½Ã 141:1 {A Psalm of David.} O Lord, I call upon Thee; hasten to me! Give ear to my voice when I call to Thee!
19½Ã 141:2 May my prayer be counted as incense before Thee; The lifting up of my hands as the evening offering.
19½Ã 141:3 Set a guard, O LORD, over my mouth; Keep watch over the door of my lips.
19½Ã 141:4 Do not incline my heart to any evil thing, To practice deeds of wickedness With men who do iniquity; And do not let me eat of their delicacies.
19½Ã 141:5 Let the righteous smite me in kindness and reprove me; It is oil upon the head; Do not let my head refuse it, For still my prayer is against their wicked deeds.
19½Ã 141:6 Their judges are thrown down by the sides of the rock, And they hear my words, for they are pleasant.
19½Ã 141:7 As when one plows and breaks open the earth, Our bones have been scattered at the mouth of Sheol.
19½Ã 141:8 For my eyes are toward Thee, O GOD, the Lord; In Thee I take refuge; do not leave me defenseless.
19½Ã 141:9 Keep me from the jaws of the trap which they have set for me, And from the snares of those who do iniquity.
19½Ã 141:10 Let the wicked fall into their own nets, While I pass by safely.
19½Ã 142:1 {Maskil of David, when he was in the cave. A Prayer.} I cry aloud with my voice to the LORD; I make supplication with my voice to the LORD.
19½Ã 142:2 I pour out my complaint before Him; I declare my trouble before Him.
19½Ã 142:3 When my spirit was overwhelmed within me, Thou didst know my path. In the way where I walk They have hidden a trap for me.
19½Ã 142:4 Look to the right and see; For there is no one who regards me; There is no escape for me; No one cares for my soul.
19½Ã 142:5 I cried out to Thee, O LORD; I said, "Thou art my refuge, My portion in the land of the living.
19½Ã 142:6 "Give heed to my cry, For I am brought very low; Deliver me from my persecutors, For they are too strong for me.
19½Ã 142:7 "Bring my soul out of prison, So that I may give thanks to Thy name; The righteous will surround me, For Thou wilt deal bountifully with me."
19½Ã 143:1 {A Psalm of David.} Hear my prayer, O LORD, Give ear to my supplications! Answer me in Thy faithfulness, in Thy righteousness!
19½Ã 143:2 And do not enter into judgment with Thy servant, For in Thy sight no man living is righteous.
19½Ã 143:3 For the enemy has persecuted my soul; He has crushed my life to the ground; He has made me dwell in dark places, like those who have long been dead.
19½Ã 143:4 Therefore my spirit is overwhelmed within me; My heart is appalled within me.
19½Ã 143:5 I remember the days of old; I meditate on all Thy doings; I muse on the work of Thy hands.
19½Ã 143:6 I stretch out my hands to Thee; My soul [longs] for Thee, as a parched land. Selah.
19½Ã 143:7 Answer me quickly, O LORD, my spirit fails; Do not hide Thy face from me, Lest I become like those who go down to the pit.
19½Ã 143:8 Let me hear Thy lovingkindness in the morning; For I trust in Thee; Teach me the way in which I should walk; For to Thee I lift up my soul.
19½Ã 143:9 Deliver me, O LORD, from my enemies; I take refuge in Thee.
19½Ã 143:10 Teach me to do Thy will, For Thou art my God; Let Thy good Spirit lead me on level ground.
19½Ã 143:11 For the sake of Thy name, O LORD, revive me. In Thy righteousness bring my soul out of trouble.
19½Ã 143:12 And in Thy lovingkindness cut off my enemies, And destroy all those who afflict my soul; For I am Thy servant.
19½Ã 144:1 {[A Psalm] of David.} Blessed be the LORD, my rock, Who trains my hands for war, [And] my fingers for battle;
19½Ã 144:2 My lovingkindness and my fortress, My stronghold and my deliverer; My shield and He in whom I take refuge; Who subdues my people under me.
19½Ã 144:3 O LORD, what is man, that Thou dost take knowledge of him? Or the son of man, that Thou dost think of him?
19½Ã 144:4 Man is like a mere breath; His days are like a passing shadow.
19½Ã 144:5 Bow Thy heavens, O LORD, and come down; Touch the mountains, that they may smoke.
19½Ã 144:6 Flash forth lightning and scatter them; Send out Thine arrows and confuse them.
19½Ã 144:7 Stretch forth Thy hand from on high; Rescue me and deliver me out of great waters, Out of the hand of aliens
19½Ã 144:8 Whose mouths speak deceit, And whose right hand is a right hand of falsehood.
19½Ã 144:9 I will sing a new song to Thee, O God; Upon a harp of ten strings I will sing praises to Thee,
19½Ã 144:10 Who dost give salvation to kings; Who dost rescue David His servant from the evil sword.
19½Ã 144:11 Rescue me, and deliver me out of the hand of aliens, Whose mouth speaks deceit, And whose right hand is a right hand of falsehood.
19½Ã 144:12 Let our sons in their youth be as grown-up plants, And our daughters as corner pillars fashioned as for a palace;
19½Ã 144:13 [Let] our garners be full, furnishing every kind of produce, [And] our flocks bring forth thousands and ten thousands in our fields;
19½Ã 144:14 [Let] our cattle bear, Without mishap and without loss, [Let there be] no outcry in our streets!
19½Ã 144:15 How blessed are the people who are so situated; How blessed are the people whose God is the LORD!
19½Ã 145:1 {[A Psalm of] Praise, of David.} I will extol Thee, my God, O King; And I will bless Thy name forever and ever.
19½Ã 145:2 Every day I will bless Thee, And I will praise Thy name forever and ever.
19½Ã 145:3 Great is the LORD, and highly to be praised; And His greatness is unsearchable.
19½Ã 145:4 One generation shall praise Thy works to another, And shall declare Thy mighty acts.
19½Ã 145:5 On the glorious splendor of Thy majesty, And on Thy wonderful works, I will meditate.
19½Ã 145:6 And men shall speak of the power of Thine awesome acts; And I will tell of Thy greatness.
19½Ã 145:7 They shall eagerly utter the memory of Thine abundant goodness, And shall shout joyfully of Thy righteousness.
19½Ã 145:8 The LORD is gracious and merciful; Slow to anger and great in lovingkindness.
19½Ã 145:9 The LORD is good to all, And His mercies are over all His works.
19½Ã 145:10 All Thy works shall give thanks to Thee, O LORD, And Thy godly ones shall bless Thee.
19½Ã 145:11 They shall speak of the glory of Thy kingdom, And talk of Thy power;
19½Ã 145:12 To make known to the sons of men Thy mighty acts, And the glory of the majesty of Thy kingdom.
19½Ã 145:13 Thy kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, And Thy dominion [endures] throughout all generations.
19½Ã 145:14 The LORD sustains all who fall, And raises up all who are bowed down.
19½Ã 145:15 The eyes of all look to Thee, And Thou dost give them their food in due time.
19½Ã 145:16 Thou dost open Thy hand, And dost satisfy the desire of every living thing.
19½Ã 145:17 The LORD is righteous in all His ways, And kind in all His deeds.
19½Ã 145:18 The LORD is near to all who call upon Him, To all who call upon Him in truth.
19½Ã 145:19 He will fulfill the desire of those who fear Him; He will also hear their cry and will save them.
19½Ã 145:20 The LORD keeps all who love Him; But all the wicked, He will destroy.
19½Ã 145:21 My mouth will speak the praise of the LORD; And all flesh will bless His holy name forever and ever.
19½Ã 146:1 Praise the LORD! Praise the LORD, O my soul!
19½Ã 146:2 I will praise the LORD while I live; I will sing praises to my God while I have my being.
19½Ã 146:3 Do not trust in princes, In mortal man, in whom there is no salvation.
19½Ã 146:4 His spirit departs, he returns to the earth; In that very day his thoughts perish.
19½Ã 146:5 How blessed is he whose help is the God of Jacob, Whose hope is in the LORD his God;
19½Ã 146:6 Who made heaven and earth, The sea and all that is in them; Who keeps faith forever;
19½Ã 146:7 Who executes justice for the oppressed; Who gives food to the hungry. The LORD sets the prisoners free.
19½Ã 146:8 The LORD opens [the eyes of] the blind; The LORD raises up those who are bowed down; The LORD loves the righteous;
19½Ã 146:9 The LORD protects the strangers; He supports the fatherless and the widow; But He thwarts the way of the wicked.
19½Ã 146:10 The LORD will reign forever, Thy God, O Zion, to all generations. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 147:1 Praise the LORD! For it is good to sing praises to our God; For it is pleasant [and] praise is becoming.
19½Ã 147:2 The LORD builds up Jerusalem; He gathers the outcasts of Israel.
19½Ã 147:3 He heals the brokenhearted, And binds up their wounds.
19½Ã 147:4 He counts the number of the stars; He gives names to all of them.
19½Ã 147:5 Great is our Lord, and abundant in strength; His understanding is infinite.
19½Ã 147:6 The LORD supports the afflicted; He brings down the wicked to the ground.
19½Ã 147:7 Sing to the LORD with thanksgiving; Sing praises to our God on the lyre,
19½Ã 147:8 Who covers the heavens with clouds, Who provides rain for the earth, Who makes grass to grow on the mountains.
19½Ã 147:9 He gives to the beast its food, [And] to the young ravens which cry.
19½Ã 147:10 He does not delight in the strength of the horse; He does not take pleasure in the legs of a man.
19½Ã 147:11 The LORD favors those who fear Him, Those who wait for His lovingkindness.
19½Ã 147:12 Praise the LORD, O Jerusalem! Praise your God, O Zion!
19½Ã 147:13 For He has strengthened the bars of your gates; He has blessed your sons within you.
19½Ã 147:14 He makes peace in your borders; He satisfies you with the finest of the wheat.
19½Ã 147:15 He sends forth His command to the earth; His word runs very swiftly.
19½Ã 147:16 He gives snow like wool; He scatters the frost like ashes.
19½Ã 147:17 He casts forth His ice as fragments; Who can stand before His cold?
19½Ã 147:18 He sends forth His word and melts them; He causes His wind to blow and the waters to flow.
19½Ã 147:19 He declares His words to Jacob, His statutes and His ordinances to Israel.
19½Ã 147:20 He has not dealt thus with any nation; And as for His ordinances, they have not known them. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 148:1 Praise the LORD! Praise the LORD from the heavens; Praise Him in the heights!
19½Ã 148:2 Praise Him, all His angels; Praise Him, all His hosts!
19½Ã 148:3 Praise Him, sun and moon; Praise Him, all stars of light!
19½Ã 148:4 Praise Him, highest heavens, And the waters that are above the heavens!
19½Ã 148:5 Let them praise the name of the LORD, For He commanded and they were created.
19½Ã 148:6 He has also established them forever and ever; He has made a decree which will not pass away.
19½Ã 148:7 Praise the LORD from the earth, Sea monsters and all deeps;
19½Ã 148:8 Fire and hail, snow and clouds; Stormy wind, fulfilling His word;
19½Ã 148:9 Mountains and all hills; Fruit trees and all cedars;
19½Ã 148:10 Beasts and all cattle; Creeping things and winged fowl;
19½Ã 148:11 Kings of the earth and all peoples; Princes and all judges of the earth;
19½Ã 148:12 Both young men and virgins; Old men and children.
19½Ã 148:13 Let them praise the name of the LORD, For His name alone is exalted; His glory is above earth and heaven.
19½Ã 148:14 And He has lifted up a horn for His people, Praise for all His godly ones; [Even] for the sons of Israel, a people near to Him. Praise the LORD !
19½Ã 149:1 Praise the LORD! Sing to the LORD a new song, And His praise in the congregation of the godly ones.
19½Ã 149:2 Let Israel be glad in his Maker; Let the sons of Zion rejoice in their King.
19½Ã 149:3 Let them praise His name with dancing; Let them sing praises to Him with timbrel and lyre.
19½Ã 149:4 For the LORD takes pleasure in His people; He will beautify the afflicted ones with salvation.
19½Ã 149:5 Let the godly ones exult in glory; Let them sing for joy on their beds.
19½Ã 149:6 [Let] the high praises of God [be] in their mouth, And a two-edged sword in their hand,
19½Ã 149:7 To execute vengeance on the nations, And punishment on the peoples;
19½Ã 149:8 To bind their kings with chains, And their nobles with fetters of iron;
19½Ã 149:9 To execute on them the judgment written; This is an honor for all His godly ones. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 150:1 Praise the LORD! Praise God in His sanctuary; Praise Him in His mighty expanse.
19½Ã 150:2 Praise Him for His mighty deeds; Praise Him according to His excellent greatness.
19½Ã 150:3 Praise Him with trumpet sound; Praise Him with harp and lyre.
19½Ã 150:4 Praise Him with timbrel and dancing; Praise Him with stringed instruments and pipe.
19½Ã 150:5 Praise Him with loud cymbals; Praise Him with resounding cymbals.
19½Ã 150:6 Let everything that has breath praise the LORD. Praise the LORD!
