22¾Æ 1:16 "How handsome you are, my beloved, [And] so pleasant! Indeed, our couch is luxuriant!
22¾Æ 1:17 "The beams of our houses are cedars, Our rafters, cypresses.
22¾Æ 2:1 "I am the rose of Sharon, The lily of the valleys."
22¾Æ 2:2 "Like a lily among the thorns, So is my darling among the maidens."
22¾Æ 2:3 "Like an apple tree among the trees of the forest, So is my beloved among the young men. In his shade I took great delight and sat down, And his fruit was sweet to my taste.
22¾Æ 2:4 "He has brought me to [his] banquet hall, And his banner over me is love.
22¾Æ 2:5 "Sustain me with raisin cakes, Refresh me with apples, Because I am lovesick.
22¾Æ 2:6 "[Let] his left hand be under my head And his right hand embrace me."
22¾Æ 2:7 "I adjure you, O daughters of Jerusalem, By the gazelles or by the hinds of the field, That you will not arouse or awaken [my] love, Until she pleases."
22¾Æ 2:8 "Listen! My beloved! Behold, he is coming, Climbing on the mountains, Leaping on the hills!
