22¾Æ 2:13 'The fig tree has ripened its figs, And the vines in blossom have given forth [their] fragrance. Arise, my darling, my beautiful one, And come along!' "
22¾Æ 2:14 "O my dove, in the clefts of the rock, In the secret place of the steep pathway, Let me see your form, Let me hear your voice; For your voice is sweet, And your form is lovely."
22¾Æ 2:15 "Catch the foxes for us, The little foxes that are ruining the vineyards, While our vineyards are in blossom."
22¾Æ 2:16 "My beloved is mine, and I am his; He pastures [his flock] among the lilies.
22¾Æ 2:17 "Until the cool of the day when the shadows flee away, Turn, my beloved, and be like a gazelle Or a young stag on the mountains of Bether."
22¾Æ 3:1 "On my bed night after night I sought him Whom my soul loves; I sought him but did not find him.
22¾Æ 3:2 'I must arise now and go about the city; In the streets and in the squares I must seek him whom my soul loves.' I sought him but did not find him.
22¾Æ 3:3 "The watchmen who make the rounds in the city found me, [And I said,] ' Have you seen him whom my soul loves? '
22¾Æ 3:4 "Scarcely had I left them When I found him whom my soul loves; I held on to him and would not let him go, Until I had brought him to my mother's house, And into the room of her who conceived me."
22¾Æ 3:5 "I adjure you, O daughters of Jerusalem, By the gazelles or by the hinds of the field, That you will not arouse or awaken [my] love, Until she pleases."
22¾Æ 3:6 "What is this coming up from the wilderness Like columns of smoke, Perfumed with myrrh and frankincense, With all scented powders of the merchant?
22¾Æ 3:7 "Behold, it is the [traveling] couch of Solomon; Sixty mighty men around it, Of the mighty men of Israel.
22¾Æ 3:8 "All of them are wielders of the sword, Expert in war; Each man has his sword at his side, [Guarding] against the terrors of the night.
22¾Æ 3:9 "King Solomon has made for himself a sedan chair From the timber of Lebanon.
22¾Æ 3:10 "He made its posts of silver, Its back of gold [And] its seat of purple fabric, [With] its interior lovingly fitted out By the daughters of Jerusalem.
22¾Æ 3:11 "Go forth, O daughters of Zion, And gaze on King Solomon with the crown With which his mother has crowned him On the day of his wedding, And on the day of his gladness of heart."
22¾Æ 4:1 "How beautiful you are, my darling, How beautiful you are! Your eyes are [like] doves behind your veil; Your hair is like a flock of goats That have descended from Mount Gilead.
22¾Æ 4:2 "Your teeth are like a flock of [newly] shorn ewes Which have come up from [their] washing, All of which bear twins, And not one among them has lost her young.
22¾Æ 4:3 "Your lips are like a scarlet thread, And your mouth is lovely. Your temples are like a slice of a pomegranate Behind your veil.
22¾Æ 4:4 "Your neck is like the tower of David Built with rows of stones, On which are hung a thousand shields, All the round shields of the mighty men.
22¾Æ 4:5 "Your two breasts are like two fawns, Twins of a gazelle, Which feed among the lilies.
22¾Æ 4:6 "Until the cool of the day When the shadows flee away, I will go my way to the mountain of myrrh And to the hill of frankincense.
22¾Æ 4:7 "You are altogether beautiful, my darling, And there is no blemish in you.
22¾Æ 4:8 "[Come] with me from Lebanon, [my] bride, May you come with me from Lebanon. Journey down from the summit of Amana, From the summit of Senir and Hermon, From the dens of lions, From the mountains of leopards.
22¾Æ 4:9 "You have made my heart beat faster, my sister, [my] bride; You have made my heart beat faster with a single [glance] of your eyes, With a single strand of your necklace.
22¾Æ 4:10 "How beautiful is your love, my sister, [my] bride! How much better is your love than wine, And the fragrance of your oils Than all [kinds] of spices!
22¾Æ 4:11 "Your lips, [my] bride, drip honey; Honey and milk are under your tongue, And the fragrance of your garments is like the fragrance of Lebanon.
22¾Æ 4:12 "A garden locked is my sister, [my] bride, A rock garden locked, a spring sealed up.
22¾Æ 4:13 "Your shoots are an orchard of pomegranates With choice fruits, henna with nard plants,
22¾Æ 4:14 Nard and saffron, calamus and cinnamon, With all the trees of frankincense, Myrrh and aloes, along with all the finest spices.
